title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Put the evaporated milk in freezer for 1/2 hour.
Dissolve the jello and sugar in boiling water in a separate bowl.
With electric beaters, whip evaporated milk until doubled in volume. Add cream cheese; whip.
Add dissolved jello mixture, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour mixture evenly into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish lined with crushed graham crackers.
Sprinkle top with a handful of crushed graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: tater bake
directions: Prepare large double foil wrap.
Cover sliced bacon with alternating layers of potatoes, onions and peppers.
Top with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper and salsa.
Cook on grill, over campfire or at 350° in RV oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: lumpia(egg rolls)
directions: In a Dutch oven pot, put 2 tablespoons of cooking oil and meat.
Cook until meat is done.
Add in a package of coleslaw mix and spices; cook for another 5 to 10 minutes, while stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and marshmallows in a bowl.
Mix Crisco, oleo, cocoa and Coke; bring to a boil.
Mix dry ingredients with it.
Stir in buttermilk with soda, add this along with eggs.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan or loaf at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in medium saucepan. Slowly mix in egg yolks. Add milk, stirring well, then butter and vanilla. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thick. Let cool slightly. Pour into baked pie crust. Cool. Serve topped with Cool Whip Light.

title: sheet cookies
directions: Boil together raisins and water until 1 cup water remains. Let cool.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix in vanilla and raisins (juice also).
Spread on 2 greased cookie sheets.
Remove and put on glaze frosting.

title: peach crisp (cobbler)
directions: Using a
13 x 9-inch buttered dish, layer peaches (apples can be used instead, if desired). Sprinkle flour, sugar and cinnamon over peaches. Put butter a little here and there.

title: china pepper steak
directions: Slice steak thinly in short crosswise pieces.
Heat butter in skillet and add garlic, salt and pepper.
Add beef and brown on both sides.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.
Cool 5 minutes and glaze.

title: peachie cream torte
directions: Line a 9-inch spring-form pan with plastic wrap.
Reserve 12 ladyfinger halves.
Line bottom and sides of pan with remaining ladyfinger halves.
Fill with half of the ice cream, then the reserved ladyfingers and then top with remaining ice cream.
Freeze at least 1 hour.
When ready to serve, remove rim of pan and plastic wrap.
Combine preserves and about 2 tablespoons of the peach juice.
Mix well.
Arrange peaches over top of ice cream; pour preserve mixture over top.
Serve.

title: slow cooker chicken, broccoli, rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil in skillet. Add chicken and saute until chicken is no longer pink. Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 2 to 3 hours. This is delicious!

title: soft cheese
directions: You will need a coarse, clean cloth (like an old tea towel), a saucepan, a spoon and two bowls.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix corn, eggs, baking powder, oil, corn meal, peppers and salt together.
Stir in shredded cheese. Pour into a greased casserole and bake for 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and baby food prunes.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: baked carrots
directions: Put carrots in casserole.
Pour rest of ingredients over. Sprinkle with chives.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain and mix with taco seasoning and follow package directions.
Mix with other ingredients; top with Western dressing.
Serve warm or cold.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Place in a covered baking dish and set to the side.
Saute butter, onion and bell pepper.
Add the broccoli, mixing well.
Then add the cheese, tomatoes and soup.
Cook until the cheese has melted.
Pour over the rice and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rice krispie meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger and onions; form into balls.
Place into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.

title: savory bread sticks
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour, cheese, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add water, milk and 1/4 cup oil to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
With spoon, stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
(For rapid rise yeast, cover kneaded dough; let rest on floured surface 10 minutes.
Proceed with recipe.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into balls.
Put on slightly greased pan. Press down with fork.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix in kettle and bring to a boil.
Add 16 cups of sliced, peeled pickles (sliced very thin).
Add 8 cups onions (sliced very thin).
Bring to a boil and put in canning jars.

title: microwave-munching peanut brittle
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, blend sugar and syrup.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes (High).
Add butter and vanilla; blend well.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes. Add baking soda; stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture on to lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: chicken soup
directions: Bake potatoes; peel, cube and add to soups.
Boil deboned chicken breasts; chip up chicken and add to soup.
Add onion flakes to desired taste.
Salt and pepper.
Heat and eat.

title: spicy toasted pecans
directions: Toss nuts with melted margarine.
Spread in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Bake in a 350° oven, stirring frequently, until toasted, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1/2 pound.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased foil, after placing foil on cookie sheet.
Put in oven 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and let them remain for 8 hours before removing.

title: herbed oyster crackers
directions: I didn't have potatoes,

title: cherry cheesecake cups
directions: Place Nabisco vanilla wafers flat side down in muffin papers. Fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While still warm, dot with cherry pie filling.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add the other ingredients and pour into large oblong greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frosted fruit dip
directions: Put cream cheese in a microwave dish.
Microwave for 30 to 40 seconds or until cream cheese softens.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Whisk oil and eggs in another large bowl until blended and smooth. Stir in apples, nuts and raisins, if using (mixture will be very stiff).
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until top is golden and a pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy ambrosia
directions: Combine
fruit, undrained, coconut and dry pudding mix. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off most of the fat.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place 1 cup sugar in an iron skillet over medium heat.
Cook and stir over low heat.
After the butter melts, increase heat until a rapid boil.
Meanwhile, sugar in iron skillet has begun to melt.
When melted sugar is light brown and completely melted, pour into the boiling mixture.
Stir constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 2 teaspoons vanilla flavoring.
Beat until icing has begun to cool and thicken.
Icing will begin to turn dull in color.
When at good spreading consistency, spread between layers and on sides.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ham) with mixer.
Spread a thin layer on one slice of ham.
Roll up and place in dish.
Repeat until all ham is used.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Slice each roll into about 8 to 10 slices.
Serve on crackers.

title: golden summer squash soup
directions: Simmer the squash and chives in broth until softened. Transfer to a blender or food processor and blend until smooth. Let cool.
Then whisk in the sour cream, yogurt, lemon juice and a dash of dill weed.
Chill thoroughly.
When ready to serve, garnish with chives.

title: greek style chicken livers
directions: Saute chicken livers and onion in oil and margarine 6 minutes or until browned.
Stir in flour and basil.
Gradually stir in broth.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles, 1 minute.
Add tomatoes.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve over rotini, macaroni twists or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter with celery and onion.
Add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Add to rice and broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: instant vanilla pudding fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and let sit overnight.

title: english pea salad
directions: Sprinkle paprika on top for garnish.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl with ice ring!
Enjoy!

title: hearty cube steak sandwiches
directions: For marinade:
Combine soft drink, onion, vinegar, marjoram and oil, thyme and soy sauce on a 13 x 9 x 2-inch utility dish. Add steaks, placing them so they do not overlap.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand in refrigerator 1 hour or more.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook half bag of noodles; drain.
Mix chicken and soups in baking dish.
Stir in noodles.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: bacon and egg spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Meanwhile, in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon to paper towel; set aside.
In drippings in skillet, cook onions until tender.
Add spaghetti and bacon to onions.
Toss until well mixed.
Stir in eggs and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Begin with lettuce and place ingredients in large salad bowl in order given.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, then pour into pie shells.
Place in fridge 2 hours to set before serving.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix Cool
Whip	and Jell-O together; add other ingredients. Chill 1 hour.

title: honeycomb chicken
directions: Boil 1 whole chicken with onions and celery; cool and debone. Chop meat in chunks.
Thicken 2 cups chicken stock with 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook 1 (8 ounce) package noodles; drain and add to chicken and thickened stock.
Add 1 cup frozen peas and 1 small jar pimento.
Pour into baking dish; top with shredded cheese and pour 1 cup half and half milk or 1 cup canned milk over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with hot rolls and a Jell-O or green salad.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Roll up chicken breasts.
Wrap each breast with 1 chipped ham slice and 1 strip of bacon.
Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Place in casserole dish.

title: lasagne
directions: Remove sausage from outer casings.
Saute sausage, ground beef, onion and garlic for 20 minutes; chop sausage.
Add sugar, salt, basil, fennel, pepper and half of parsley; mix well.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water.
Mash tomatoes.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat to simmer; cook 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop cabbage, onions, tomatoes and peppers.
Add 1/4 cup salt. Let stand overnight.
Press all salt water out.
Put mixed spices in a bag.
Add sugar and spices to vinegar and simmer until hot and well seasoned.
Remove spice bag.
Pack mixture in hot jars and cover with hot vinegar mix and seal.
Do not grind cabbage, onions, tomatoes and peppers, it will be too soft.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Put cookies in a blender (a few at a time) to make crumbs. Set aside 1/4 of the cookie crumbs for topping. Add margarine (melted) to remaining crumbs.
Mix together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together. Add 6 ounces Cool Whip and fold in.
Put on top of crust and refrigerate again.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Beat until thick. Spread on top of cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip layer. Refrigerate 3 to 5 minutes.
Use remaining 6 ounces of Cool Whip for topping. Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin; dredge in flour.
Saute in pan with a bit of olive oil.
Add half of lemon and garlic.
Saute until light brown.
Remove from pan.
Glaze pan with white wine. Return chicken to pan and add broth and squeeze on the remaining lemon.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Dice beef, onion and onion stem.
Combine all ingredients. Stir and chill.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat water and add lime Jell-O. While hot, add mayonnaise and marshmallows. Let cool. Add pineapple, celery, bananas, nuts and cherries. Pour into a rectangular dish. Chill until firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
Add beans.
Cook them.
Toss with other ingredients.
Serve with French or Italian dressing.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix and let stand at least 2 hours to blend.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Mix ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper for sauce.
Place serving size pieces of steak in greased casserole dish.
Pour sauce over steak.
Top with onion slices. Sprinkle with garlic flakes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cracker crumbs; drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash romaine and dry between paper towels.
Break up pieces. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add croutons and fresh pepper.

title: homemade hard candy
directions: *I usually find oil flavorings in drug stores; common flavors are cinnamon, peppermint, clove, banana, orange, etc.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; mix well. Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 4 layers at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: layered dip
directions: Cover bottom of large platter with a thin layer of bean dip, using entire can.
Add layers of ingredients as follows:
avocados with 1 teaspoon lemon juice layer, sour cream with 1 tablespoon chili powder layer, chopped tomatoes layer, green onion layer, green pepper layer
and grated Cheddar cheese layer.
Garnish top with sliced olives.

title: upside-down orange french toast
directions: Melt butter in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Mix the next 3 ingredients; sprinkle over butter.
Place bread slices over mixture.
Mix eggs and orange juice in blender; pour over bread. Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: loretta's cream pie
directions: Blend all together, stirring in 9 ounces of Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Makes two 9-inch pies.
This is real good.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; reserve 1 cup of juice.
Into fruit, cut bananas; add juice to pudding mix (no milk) and cook until thick and transparent.
Cool slightly; pour over fruit and chill.
Serve cold.

title: deme's cheesecake!!
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese well in a very large bowl. Blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Fold in sour cream; blend well.
Pour into a 10-inch buttered spring-form pan.
Place in cold oven; turn heat to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour; do not open oven door!
(After 1 hour, I very carefully peek in to see if the cake has set; if not, I let it cook for another 1/2 to 3/4 hour longer, watching that it does not scorch in the pan.)
Turn off oven; leave until cool, at least 2 more hours.
Put any filling you wish over the top and enjoy!

title: pinecone bird feeder
directions: Wind a piece of wire around pinecone for hanger.
Mix small amount of peanut butter and bird seed together.
Roll pinecone in mixture; hang in tree.
Great to do in the Spring and Fall of the year.

title: hamburger and tater tots
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Mix in can of mushroom soup real good.
Put in 12 x 12-inch baking pan.
Put layer of cheese top, then line Tater Tots on top of the cheese.
Put Tater Tots close together.
Put in a 350° oven until Tater Tots are done.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake mix in sheet pan - leave in pan. Cool. Punch holes all over with fork. Mix milk, creme of coconut and pour over cake. Mix coconut and crushed pineapple with Cool Whip to frost cake. Chill.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Make cake mix following directions on box.
Melt margarine in heavy cast-iron skillet.
Mix in brown sugar and spread evenly. Arrange pineapple slices on top of brown sugar mixture.
Put cherry in center of each slice.
Pour cake batter over this. Bake at 350° until pick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes, then turn over onto cake plate.

title: homemade french dressing(very good)
directions: Mix all ingredients slowly, except oil, with mixer.
While mixing at medium speed, add oil in fine stream.
Mix about 15 minutes.
Need not refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain 2 cans whole corn and 1/2 of the third can.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach, mushroom and onion quiche
directions: Wash, chop and measure the spinach, mushrooms and onions.
In a large bowl combine the eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.
Add in the vegetables.
Shred the cheese and add to the bowl. Pour the contents of the bowl into an unbaked deep dish pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted 2 inches from the edge comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Let simmer; add to chicken or ribs.

title: summer squash icebox pickles
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Pack the vegetables tightly into quart jars.
Cover with brine.
Refrigerate.
These pickles keep well in the refrigerator for up to 3 months.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in non-dairy whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water.
With a wire whisk, blend in cranberry sauce.
Add strawberries and pineapple with natural juices.
Pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm (4 hours or overnight).
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sharryne's i can't believe it's cake!
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Cook 1 cup sugar and pineapple for 5 minutes; pour over cake while hot.
Mix pudding and cream cheese together.
Mix pudding as directed; pour over cooled pineapple. Slice bananas; layer over pudding mix.
Put Cool Whip over bananas; sprinkle coconut and pecans over Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil together for 1 minute water, sugar and cornstarch. Remove from heat and add strawberry gelatin and lemon juice. Cool slightly and add strawberries. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O.
Add oil, eggs and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add hot water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna lemon loaf(serves 6)
directions: Place lemon slices in bottom of very well-greased loaf pan. Thoroughly combine ingredients, except egg whites.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Spoon tuna mixture over lemon slices.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until center of loaf is firm.
Invert on warm platter.
Garnish with parsley.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown the sausage and drain. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, with points toward the center. Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations. Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with hash browns. Top with Cheddar cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour into crust. Sprinkle Parmesan over all. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Enjoy!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place apples in mixing bowl and add sugar.
Stir to mix and let stand at least 30 minutes.
Add oil and eggs to apples and stir to blend.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Combine Ranch mix, salt, garlic powder and oil.
Place pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Coat pretzels with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Stir lightly and bake 5 minutes more.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, brown sugar and egg; add melted chocolate to mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato and onion bake
directions: Peel, slice and soak potatoes for several hours.
Drain potatoes and layer in Pam sprayed casserole (deep is better) in this order:
potatoes, sliced onions and seasoned salt and repeat. Bake at 350°, covered, until potatoes are done or on High power of microwave oven.
The amount of potatoes and onions is judged by the size of your family.

title: spinach-cheese fish bake
directions: Arrange fish squares in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook frozen spinach according to package directions; drain.
Combine drained spinach, cheese soup, milk and nutmeg.
Heat; spoon over fish in baking dish.
Garnish with lemon wedges; return to oven for 5 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: golden potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine potatoes and golden onion recipe soup mix, blended with milk, water and mustard.
Microwave covered at High (Full power)
9 minutes.
Stir in cheese and microwave 5 minutes.
Stir, then let stand covered 5 minutes longer.
And watch it disappear!

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Tear or cut into pieces the cake and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add jello to 1 cup of boiling water and dissolve.
Add 1 cup of cold water and the 3 cartons of strawberries (partly thawed). Pour over cake and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours until set.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: peach smoothy
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.

title: finger paint
directions: Combine flour, salt and cold water.
Beat the mixture with an egg beater until smooth.
Add 2 cups hot water and boil until mixture becomes clear.
Beat until smooth; then add food coloring, about 1/4 teaspoon to 1 cup paint.

title: moist chocolate cake(amy michael's favorite)
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil and add to dry ingredients.
Combine with buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until tests done (the batter will be very thin).

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Beat egg whites, 3 tablespoons sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese until soft.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites. Melt margarine and add to cracker crumbs.
Put 3/4 of crumbs in greased and floured spring-form pan.
Add cheese mixture.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: meat calzone
directions: Roll dough into large rectangle.
Mix meats, cheese and sauce. Pour onto dough, keeping away from edges.
Fold dough over meat. Moisten edges to seal.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place butter and onion in a 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Roast onion, uncovered, in a 400° oven until pale gold, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Push onion to one section of pan, then place thighs, side by side in pan, but not on onion.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes longer.
In a bowl, stir together ketchup, sugar, vinegar, mustard and cranberries.
Remove chicken from oven and scoop browned onions from pan and stir them into cranberry mixture.
Space chicken evenly in pan and spoon cranberry mixture over thighs. Bake until mixture is slightly caramelized and chicken is no longer pink at bone in thickest part (cut to test), about 20 minutes.

title: salmon and biscuits
directions: Mix the biscuit mix as directed.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese. Roll out and cut.
Spread salmon in biscuit pan and add milk and 1/2 stick butter.
Slice boiled eggs sand place in salmon mix. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place rolled biscuits on top to cover pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Add sliced butter on top. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a 1 1/2 quart saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt, and pepper.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 1/2 cup cheese; stir until melted.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni and cheese sauce; turn into casserole. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Make syrup of sugar and boiling water.
Add gelatin to hot syrup.
Stir.
Cool.
Mix in lemonade, orange juice, pineapple juice, water and almond extract.
Freeze in 5 (1/2 gallon) milk cartons.
Thaw for 3 hours.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale. Punch will be slushy.

title: hominy grits and cheese
directions: Into 6 cups boiling water, add grits and boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt, butter, cheese and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10. May be made the day before and kept in refrigerator or may be frozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix
instant pudding and pineapple.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute the onion, celery and broccoli in the butter for 3-5 minutes.
Combine the cheese, soup and milk, stirring until smooth, then add to the broccoli mixture.
Place rice in a greased 8 inch square baking dish. Pour the cheese and broccoli
mixture over the rice - DO NOT STIR. Bake at 325° for 25-30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: crunchy sandwich filling
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together in bowl until creamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Yields 40 servings.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.

title: quick berry trifle
directions: Combine berries and sugar in medium bowl, stirring gently to combine.
Place single layer of cake slices in bottom of deep serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 of pudding, then 1/3 of berries. Repeat layers twice, using remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Just before serving, remove from refrigerator. Top with whipped topping.
Serve as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chinese pancakes
directions: You will also need aluminum foil.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In blender, mix all ingredients except ground meat until smooth.
Add blended liquid to meat and mix with your hands until mixture is free of lumps.
Pat into loaf pan. Bake for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 275° and continue baking an additional 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip into a large glass baking dish (rectangular). Combine sour cream and taco mix in a bowl; set aside.
Prepare guacamole by mashing with lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste. Spread on top of bean dip.
Spread sour cream mix on top of guacamole.
Sprinkle onion slices, tomatoes and olives on top. Finally sprinkle on cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: midwest barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour on top of roast in a large roasting pan.
Cover tightly. Roast at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and oleo; this will be stiff. Spread in bottom of greased rectangular pan.
Mix together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free chocolate balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts or coconut.
Blend until smooth.
Shape into balls and roll into either coconut or nuts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and margarine; bring to a boil. Beat eggs and gradually add syrup mixture.
Add nut meats, salt and vanilla extract.
Pour into pastry shell and bake.
If you want to make 2 pies, just double the ingredients.

title: weight watcher's apple brown betty
directions: Grease a shallow dish with cooking oil.
Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs to coat the surface; reserve the remaining bread crumbs.
Grate 1 teaspoon of lemon skin and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice from the lemon.
Set the juice aside.
In a small dish, combine the lemon skin, sugar and cinnamon.
Peel and core the apples, then cut them into thin slices.

title: butter 'n herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and brush on top of chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and paprika.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes applying more butter or drippings halfway through cooking time.
When done, sprinkle lightly with more garlic salt and paprika if desired.

title: mock crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Place biscuits on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass, then bake as directed on cans.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Top each section with mayonnaise mixture.
Place under broiler until lightly browned and serve immediately.

title: cheese straws
directions: Finely grate the cheese.
Combine with other ingredients and beat until creamy, adding a few drops of water, if necessary, to form a firm dough.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Boil until soft boil stage.

title: baked scallops
directions: Mix soup and wine.
Place scallops in casserole.
Pour on the soup and wine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Blend crackers and butter; spread on top of scallops.
Bake for another 15 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven; heat to boiling over high heat, stirring frequently.
Boil, uncovered, continuing to stir frequently, until mixture is translucent and jam is thick (about 25 minutes).
Quickly skim off foam and immediately pour jam into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe rim of jars.
Seal as directed.
Yields about 5 half-pints of jam.

title: italian rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, sugar, rice, water and salt in heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes, until rice is tender and desired consistency is reached.
Stir frequently during cooking.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
May be served warm or chilled with milk or whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sylvia's carrot salad
directions: Clean, peel and shred carrots.
Add raisins and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container. Cover and process until smooth. Pour into saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter roll "candy"
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla and margarine into a stiff dough. Roll out on waxed paper.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll out in long roll.
Slice and chill for several hours.
Ready to eat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Start creaming with mixer. Add cream cheese, sour cream and onion.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top off with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable bars
directions: *Broccoli, scallions, carrot, red pepper, olives, etc.

title: chinese egg roll pouches
directions: Put 1 tablespoon peanut oil in a cast-iron skillet and heat high for 1 minute.
Add carrot and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in green onions and next 6 ingredients.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to cabbage mixture and cook 1 minute or until thickened.
Let cool and spoon mixture evenly into centers of egg roll wrappers.
Moisten edges with water.
Bring ends to the middle, pressing together in center.
Pull ends up and out to resemble a pouch.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Combine crackers, pecans and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in remaining sugar and vanilla.
Fold into cracker mixture.
Spread in greased 9-inch pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add chopped onion and cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Place pretzels in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a large tube or Bundt pan.
Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco with 2 eggs (cream well together).
Add remaining eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour to mixture, alternating with 7-Up.
Add the vanilla. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place oven rack in lower position as cake will not bake properly if rack is in center of oven.
When done allow cake to cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem berries and set aside.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Mix together in saucepan the water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook, stirring constantly until clear.
Add gelatin.
Stir thoroughly and set aside to cool.

title: baked chicken with almonds
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and place in shallow baking dish.
Mix soups together and add wine.
Mix.
Cover chicken with 2/3 of the almonds and then pour soup over.
Sprinkle Parmesan and remainder of almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve with rice or buttered noodles.
Check before 2 hours, because it may dry out before 2 hours are up.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: Mix beef and bouillon cubes together; brown in soup pan with onions.
Add stewed tomatoes and Veg-All.
Fill up Veg-All can with water and add.
Add sugar, salt and orzo.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: spicy orange cider
directions: Mix together Tang, cinnamon and nutmeg in a coffee cup.
Heat apple juice and pour into cup; stir.
Add lemon slice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well and cream butter in mixture. Add dry ingredients before you mix eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: elayne's super rice
directions: Put all ingredients into a large (ovensafe) bowl.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or this can be cooked in the microwave on High about 20 to 25 minutes.
Bon Appetit!

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set awhile before serving so flavors can mix together.

title: chicken casserole(from maureen lyons)
directions: Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Line bottom of casserole with half of the buttered stuffing mix.
Place half of the chicken on top of stuffing mix.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice 6 cooked, peeled sweet potatoes into a baking dish.
In a pot mix brown sugar, butter, water, salt and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and/or nutmeg mixture (optional).

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Melt oleo and add marshmallows.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Add food coloring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and almond.
Stir in corn flakes.
Shape into wreaths on wax paper and top with candied red hots.
Keep hands coated in butter to make wreaths.

title: gene's beans, bernie's beans, ray's beans
directions: Fry down ground beef with a teaspoon of garlic and the onions. Fry bacon crisp and chop into small bits. Mix all ingredients together and bake for 2 hours at 300° in a shallow pan. Beans should form a glaze on top.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Melt margarine, cocoa and water in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs, milk and soda.
Gradually add flour mixture to cocoa mixture.
Add vanilla last.
Mix all with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased cookie sheet.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.

title: honey green beans almondine
directions: In saucepan filled with lightly salted boiling water, cook green beans for 5 minutes.
Drain; season with salt and pepper and set aside.
In skillet, melt butter and saute almonds.
Blend in honey.
Add green beans and parsley; stir and serve.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: strawberry dessert bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Put in a large bowl and make a deep well in the center.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Stir in carefully, just enough to dampen all ingredients.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Mix eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir oatmeal into dry ingredients.
Combine flour mixture with creamed mixture and set aside.

title: wild rice
directions: Saute onions and green pepper until transparent.
Add mushrooms, pimiento and slivered almonds.
Remove from heat. Gently fold into rice.
Use heated dishes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat the egg yolks and add the flour, 1 teaspoon salt and a little pepper.
Add the corn and fold in the slightly beaten egg whites.
Drop small spoonfuls on greased griddle or frying pan. Do not cook too fast.

title: pineapple banana pie
directions: Warm Glucerna in microwave oven (using a microwave-safe container) for approximately 1 minute on high setting.
DO NOT BOIL.
Pour Glucerna into blender and add gelatin on high speed. Blend for 15 seconds.
Pour blended mixture into medium bowl and stir in sour cream.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add instant pie filling mix.
Stir until well blended.
Layer sliced banana on bottom of pie crust.
Pour pineapple mixture over bananas. Refrigerate at least two hours prior to serving.

title: busy day barbecue
directions: Cut luncheon meat in thin strips.
Cook onion in a little hot fat until just tender.
Add catsup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and salt; add meat strips and heat to boiling.
Spoon over hot fluffy rice.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup water.
Add 1 chopped onion, at this point.
Add bouillon cubes.
Do not drain.
In blender, process milk, cheese and flour.
Add half and half (may also add 1 small can mushrooms here).
Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix water and fat and heat the mixture until water boils.
Add all the flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir and cook until well blended, until paste does not stick to side of pan.
While mixture is hot, add eggs, unbeaten, one at a time.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
When baked, slit one side and fill with cream or chocolate filling.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Rub into this, cold grease.
Stir in water.
Roll out; cut.
Bake in reflector oven 20 to 25 minutes. Bake in a closed oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Place popped corn in large bowl.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and cook to hard ball stage (254°).
Pour slowly over popped corn.
Mix quickly.
Butter hands and shape into 2 1/4-inch balls.
Makes about 12.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place water, rice and salt in saucepan; cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
In small skillet, saute celery and onions in butter.

title: cheese veal cutlets
directions: Beat eggs; set aside in a bowl.
Mix next 5 ingredients in a medium-size bowl.
Lightly sprinkle flour on cutlets.
Dip in egg. Coat with dry mixture.
Fry.

title: bread pudding
directions: Start combining the pieces of bread with the scalded milk and cream.
Beat the eggs and sugar; mix well.
Stir in the bread mixture.
Add the vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in the melted butter and raisins.
Pour the mixture into a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Set in a pan of warm water, about 1-inch deep.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until knife cut in center comes out clean dry.

title: stuffed spinach tomatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice from the top of each tomato.
Scoop out and discard pulp.
Sprinkle inside with salt and turn upside down to drain for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Defrost spinach and drain well. Mix bacon, spinach, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, curry powder, garlic powder and enough melted butter to moisten.
Stuff tomatoes with mixture, place in buttered baking dish and drizzle with small amount of butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with sour cream and serve.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice. Add tapioca and apples. Simmer until tender. Add cinnamon and butter. Put into pie crust. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crock pot cube steak
directions: Put steak in crock pot. Mix other ingredients together and pour over steak. Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours. Delicious, served over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: In skillet, saute the beef or turkey, bacon, celery and onion for 10 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Add rice, soups, mushrooms, milk and optional ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato ahead of time.
When ready to serve, chop tomato into small pieces and add to salad.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut the cheese into cubes.
Mix all together in 2-quart oblong baking dish. Cover and bake 1 hour (stir occasionally).
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour or until lightly browned.

title: crunchy corn pie
directions: Mix corn together.
Beat egg and mix.
Put in 1 can French fried onion rings; mix in.
Put in 2-quart casseroledish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until firm.
Sprinkle rest of French fried onion rings and cook 5 minutes more.

title: pasties
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and add water to moisten the dry ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Toss together meat, potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Divide pastry in half; roll into a circle.

Put in pie plate, then filling to one side; add butter. Pull pastry over top to opposite side; seal edges tightly.	Cut slits in top; bake at 400° for 45 minutes.	Add 1 tablespoon water or cream in slits.	Reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Whip cream until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Break eggs and separate.
Beat egg yolks, slowly adding 1 cup sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved and smooth.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix well in a large bowl.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until top springs back to touch or toothpick pulls out clean).
Wrap in wax paper and foil.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: spinach dressing
directions: Mix and shake.
Delicious used on spinach salad.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package.
Boil 2 cups sugar and can of crushed pineapple for 5 minutes.
While cake is hot, punch holes in it and pour pineapple mixture over it.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over cake to ice.

title: jelly muffins
directions: Turn oven on to 400°.
Mix milk, oil and egg.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Then mix together until moist.
Fill muffin cups with 1/3 batter.
Add 1 teaspoon preserves and then more batter.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Butter a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Spread half of this in pan. Chill.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Melt butter. Mix cream cheese first.
Combine in one bowl.
Next, whip milk, instant pudding and Cool Whip together in a separate bowl.
Grind up Oreo cookies.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Fill bottom of pan with ground up Oreo cookies, then place mixture on top. Repeat.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Cook broccoli 10 minutes in unsalted water.
Cook chicken breast and cut it up. Layer Rice-A-Roni, broccoli, chicken and cheese in large 3-quart casserole dish.
Combine and heat mushroom soup, milk and margarine.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarplum pudding
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in prunes.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Pour glaze over hot cake.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Combine dressings.
Combine spaghetti and remaining ingredients except tomatoes and cheese. Pour on dressing and mix well.
Marinate overnight.
Add tomatoes and cheese just before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° until solid. Makes 2 pies.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Generously
grease
and flour bottom and sides of Bundt pan. Sprinkle
the bottom with the marshmallows.
Combine the strawberries
and jello and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine the remaining
ingredients.
Blend	on low until moistened and
beat	3
minutes on medium speed.
Pour the batter over the marshmallows.
Spoon
the
strawberry
mixture evenly over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour water over dates and add soda.
Let cool.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add date mixture to three ingredients, then add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well and put batter in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Top with the following before baking:
chocolate chips, sugar and nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix per instructions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Meanwhile, melt caramels in evaporated milk and butter over low heat.
After cake has baked for 15 minutes, then pour caramel mixture over top.

title: fruited cheesecake
directions: Mix peach syrup and water together in a small pan and bring to a boil.
In a mixing bowl, combine gelatine and sugar.
Add hot liquid.
Mix with electric mixer until gelatine and sugar are dissolved. Beat in cream cheese.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour mixture and the remaining ingredients to the oil, sugar and egg mixture.
Mix until thoroughly incorporated.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Pour original juice off dill slices; then add vinegar, celery and mustard seed.
Add sugar slowly, shaking or stirring gently so the sugar will dissolve.
Refrigerate.
They become crisp when cooled.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Mix vegetables	together in a bowl. Mix everything else in a saucepan and boil 1 minute.
Pour hot liquid over vegetables. Toss as they cool; toss several more times.
Make ahead and chill 24 hours.
Keeps refrigerated for 2 weeks or more.

title: salsa
directions: Add all the ingredients in a pan and simmer.
Cook until the desired consistency.
Serve as a dip or use as desired.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cover meat with water; add 1 tablespoon vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly until meat is very tender and can be pulled apart with a fork (approximately 2 to 3 hours).
Drain liquid from meat and tear apart with fork until fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer a few minutes more to blend flavors.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: tater tots
directions: Press ground beef in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt to taste. Sprinkle onion over ground beef; pour soup over mixture.
Place Tater Tots in single layer over mixture.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour or until meat is done.

title: philly ball
directions: Mix all together into a ball.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add dates, sugar and eggs.
Cook over low heat.
Stir until mixture forms a ball, 5 to 8 minutes. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well. Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax paper and on your hands.
Shape ingredients into rolls.
Roll in powdered sugar and chill while wrapped in wax paper.
When solid, cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: cornflake fish
directions: Season fish with salt and pepper.
Dip and coat fish in oil. Coat with crumbs.
Layer in oiled baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes without turning at 500°.

title: biscuits
directions: Place dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Add shortening.
Put seal or top on bowl and shake. Add buttermilk. Replace top and shake in clockwise motion.
Put on pastry sheets and roll to desired thickness.
Cut out and bake.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let everything get soft.
Mix all together with electric mixer. Put in refrigerator before making balls (until mixture is firm enough to handle).
Mix parsley, almonds and pecans together on a platter (1 package each ground nuts).
Roll balls in mixture until completely covered.
Pat balls with palms of hand to make sure nuts and parsley are secure.
These Cheese Balls can be frozen for a long time.
You can use part of one and re-freeze what is left.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Prepare pie crust as directed on package using a 9-inch pie pan and place bottom crust in pie plate. Set aside. In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion; cook 2 minutes, until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended. Gradually stir in broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly and thickened. Add chicken and mixed vegetables. Remove from heat. Spoon chicken mixture into crust-lined pan. Top with 2nd crust and flute. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels. Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crispy cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: grandma scolaro's thanksgiving meat stuffing
directions: Cook onion in oil in a large pan. Add the meat and cook fully. Mash crackers and add the Bell seasonings, salt and pepper. Add to the meat mix. Place in the turkey and cook.

title: chop-suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water; add Jell-O and sugar.
Let set until cool.
Add oranges, apples and pineapple.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: "healthy" banana bread
directions: Step 1:
With an electric mixer or fork or potato masher, mash bananas and add applesauce in bowl.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix and add eggs one at a time.
Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and glaze.
Blend.
In shallow dish, pour mixture over chicken pieces.
Cover and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill chicken over medium coals for 45 to 50 minutes, brushing with marinade and turning frequently.
Just before serving, brush with glaze.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in large bowl on medium speed. Stir in baking mix, cinnamon and raisins. Grease pan, 15 x 10 x 1. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: libby's corn
directions: Mix together and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Make jello according to directions, using strawberry juice. Let jello set until right consistency to whip.
Whip jello.
Fold in drained strawberries. Break up angel food cake in loaf pan. Pour jello mixture over cake.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Cook your ground beef and drain grease off.
Add your chunky tomatoes and chunky mushrooms and garlic.
Let simmer on low heat for about 1 hour.

title: heavenly orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add frozen orange juice, undiluted.
Add orange sections and pineapple.
Mix well; pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Congeal.

title: eggnog
directions: The egg may be separated and the egg yolk beaten with the salt, sugar and vanilla or the whole egg may be used.
Add the milk and, if the egg has been separated, the egg white, beaten stiff.
Mix thoroughly and serve.
A sprinkling of nutmeg may top each serving. Makes 1 glass.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no stick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in spread; coat with remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Pour over
2 (12 ounce) packages oyster crackers.
Mix well and let set for at least 1 hour.
These crackers are great for snacking, soups and chili.
Store in a sealed container for freshness.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on floured surface and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer as follows:
cream cheese on bottom of dish, chili, salsa, optional items and cheese.
Microwave 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: bacon and horseradish dip
directions: You will need to cook this soup in a five-gallon container since the recipe makes such a large quantity.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Bring to a boil; let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla, egg and grated lemon peel.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix thoroughly.

title: corn meal foldovers
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg and sour cream; mix lightly.
Turn onto floured board; knead gently just to smooth out dough.
Roll to about 1/4-inch.
Cut into 2-inch rounds.
Brush tops with melted butter.
With knife,
make crease across center and fold over, butter side in.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Add lemon juice. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep 1 week.
Use what you need and keep rest refrigerated.
These are very good rolls.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Cut and seed peppers.
Place half of peppers and half of vinegar into blender.
Blend until it liquifies.
Repeat with other half.
Place in heavy pot on top of stove.
Add cayenne pepper, sugar and food coloring.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Set aside for 2 minutes.
Add Certo; stir.
Put in half-pint jars that have boiled for 15 minutes.
Cover and place in water bath for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes about 8 half-pint jars.
This is a great appetizer using sesame rye crackers, topped with cream cheese and Pepper Jelly on top.
Very pretty at holiday season.

title: one minute fudge icing
directions: Cook until boils.
Boil one minute.
Add vanilla and beat until consistency to spread.
Enough for 2 layers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and carrots. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jane's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours if possible.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour well.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add well beaten egg yolks and butter. Cook a minute or more.
Add vanilla; cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Add orange rind and juice.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add creamed mixture.
Add oats, raisins and nuts, mixing until blended.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 36 large cookies.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 to 18.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups of flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in enough more flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with corn meal.
Cover; let stand in warm place for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cornmeal and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove immediately from pans and cool.
To serve, slice and toast. Yields 16 slices per loaf.

title: corn chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, cook all until tender.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 8 strips of bacon, cooked, drained and crumbled and 4 cups milk with 1/2 cup flour.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated and slightly thickened.
Add small amounts of milk if soup becomes too thick.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites; add 2 tablespoons sugar from the 1 1/2 cups.
Put in refrigerator.
Sift flour mixture; cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, along with bananas.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk-soda mixture alternately.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three layers for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use buttercream icing with nuts (optional).
Add candy sprinkles on top if desired.

title: vegetable and chicken pot pie(or turkey)
directions: *I usually double these ingredients.

title: southern coconut cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until foamy and gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue beating until meringue will hold up in stiff peaks.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and gradually add the 2 cups sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Add beaten egg whites and fold thoroughly into batter, 3 layers at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Place chops in pan.
Slice potatoes.
Place on pork chops. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with mixed soup and milk.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Can add 1/8 cup hot pepper, chopped fine.

title: chicken pie(club member: luke robinson)
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish. Mix chicken soup and chicken broth well; pour over chicken. Mix lightly. Add eggs, peas and carrots; mix with chicken.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix cornstarch and a little water.
Add other ingredients. Baste meat overnight.
Bake 1 hour, covered, then 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Can be served over rice or as is.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into balls (rounded teaspoonful).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth, except the salted peanuts.
Chill.
When firm enough to handle, shape into a ball. Roll ball in salted peanuts.
Chill until 30 minutes before serving.
May be wrapped in aluminum foil and frozen.

title: hobo stew
directions: Mix in a large pot.
Simmer a couple of hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat roll dough into 10 x 15-inch pan and bake about 6 minutes according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and mayonnaise until smooth.
Spread on baked and cooled dough.
Chop vegetables fine and pat on top of dressing.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Fold in sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 of batter in tube pan (greased and floured).
Cover with topping; spoon in rest of batter.
Cover with remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes (toothpick test).
Cool completely before removing.

title: suzanne's stuffed (deviled) eggs
directions: Shell and slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolk and mash all yolks together with the mayonnaise, mustards, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste until smoothly blended and creamy.
Use a pastry tube to pipe the creamy yolk mixture into the whites.
Sprinkle paprika and parsley on top, if desired.
Garnishes such as a slice of olive or pickle can make stuffed eggs particularly lovely.

title: cauliflower oriental
directions: Place cauliflower and water in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook in microwave covered on Full power 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand covered.
Combine onion, celery, parsley and butter in 1-quart dish.
Cook on Full power 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Stir halfway through.
Dissolve bouillon in water; blend in cornstarch, soy sauce and pepper.
Pour into onion mix.
Cook on Full power 2 minutes or until thick.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain cauliflower.
Place in serving dish.
Spoon sauce over.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Melt butter, then cool.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg, orange juice and water; stir in melted butter.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients; add liquid ingredients all at one time.
Stir only enough to moisten all dry ingredients.
Add nuts, dates, cranberries and orange rind.
Stir just until blended.
(Do not over mix.)
Turn into prepared loaf pan and spread to corners. Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes in pan on cooling rack.
This is a very good holiday treat.

title: marian spruill's macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring 4 cups of water to a boil. Add salt and 2 cups macaroni. Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until macaroni is done.
Drain macaroni. Place in a
large bowl. Combine cheese, eggs, milk, salt and pepper; mix with macaroni.
Pour into baking pan and sprinkle top with grated cheese, paprika and butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease Pyrex baking dish.
Put potatoes in dish.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper and spread over potatoes.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with corn flake crumbs; sprinkle on top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender and lightly browned.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to boil; cool and add vinegar.
Clean but do not peel cucumber; slice very thinly. Pour dressing over and let stand 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: sweepstake potato salad
directions: Combine diced green onions, radishes, eggs and potatoes. Blend remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly with potato mixture. Chill. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: peas and rice
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, cook bacon 3 minutes. Add onions and green peppers. Cook 2 minutes. Add garlic; cook another minute. Add remaining ingredients. Reduce heat and cover until water is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: tasty taters
directions: Peel and slice potatoes like for potato salad.
Cook in skillet with margarine over medium heat.
Add some water if needed.
When tender, add other ingredients.
Simmer ten minutes.

title: santa's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: fudgy chocolate pie(no crust)
directions: Beat eggs and beat in sugar and butter.
Stir the flour, cocoa and salt into the egg mixture.
Beat well until well blended. Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts and pour into the buttered pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until it is set.
(Toothpick test doesn't work in this recipe.)
Cool completely before cutting.

title: creamy chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and milk.
Start beating and add egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) deep dish baked pie crusts and top with meringue.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Add liquid from Mushrooms to Mushroom Soup.
Then into a casserole dish put 2 layers in this order:
Green Beans; 1/2 of Mushrooms; 1/2 of Cheese; a little Mushroom Soup; a few Onion Rings.
Repeat; reserve most Onion Rings for top.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
Keep in freezer when not being served.
Makes a most delicious salad for the holidays.

title: italian beef supper
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Add salt, tomato sauce, V-8 juice and water; bring to boil.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mock cherry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients about 10 minutes.
Thicken mixture with cornstarch, dissolved in a little water.
Then add vanilla. Pour filling into a pastry lined pan.
Cover top with pastry and crimp edges.
Cut large circle in top about 2-inches for steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and 350° for 40 minutes. Cover top with foil when half baked to prevent pie from becoming too brown.

title: aunt evelyn's cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large pot, saute onion, celery, carrots, potato and garlic in margarine. Add broccoli and chicken broth. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Puree mixture in blender, one cup at a time; return to pot. Add milk, marjoram, vegetable seasoning, lemon herb seasoning and pepper. Cook over low temperature (heat), stirring often until of serving temperature.

title: corn cakes and corn syrup
directions: In a small saucepan, heat the syrup and 1 cup of the corn kernels over low heat until the corn is tender and the mixture is heated through, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna potato chip casserole
directions: Reserve a few potato chips for garnish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a small casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in casserole. Sprinkle reserved chips on top.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: If using frozen tortillas, thaw.
In a large heavy skillet brown meat on low heat.
Chop onion fine and mince garlic.
Add to meat.
Cook until tender; add chili powder and tomato sauce. Simmer about 5 minutes.
If too dry, add more paste.
Lightly grease bottom of deep casserole dish.
Place one tortilla in dish; spoon mixture on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue with all 6 tortillas.
Pour hot water around the sides, cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers and onions; sprinkle salt over top and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender on medium heat, about 30 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
I double vinegar and spice mixture for this recipe.	Makes 8 pints.

title: anisette sponge dessert
directions: Slice each sponge in half lengthwise.
Lay sponge in 9 x 13-inch (glass preferred) pan to cover bottom.
Sprinkle with the rum.
Set aside.
Mix instant chocolate pudding according to package instructions but do not let it stand.
Pour directly over the sponge. Be sure that it covers all the sponge.
Mix vanilla instant the same and pour it over the chocolate, being careful not to make a hole in the chocolate layer.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble it. Add sugar and vinegar to drippings. In casserole dish layer green beans. bacon and onions. Pour prepared drippings over green beans in casserole dish and refrigerate overnight. Bake the next day at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Stir once while baking.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until sauce is thick (45 minutes to 1 hour), stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Use salad oil in cooking water to keep noodles from sticking together.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Add pecans and extra can of chocolate syrup.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Place first nine ingredients in large pot; bring to boil and add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Other shellfish like crab and clams may be added, if desired.

title: grandmother's applesauce bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in applesauce and nuts.
Grease and flour loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chewy oatmeal potato chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Mix butter flavor Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Mix oats and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in potato chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking pan.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: double corn cakes
directions: Stir pancake mix and cornmeal.
Combine corn, milk, eggs and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Drop batter from 1/4 cup measure onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn once. Makes 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: pecan squares
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar in bowl. Cut in butter. Press mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large Dutch oven, mix meat, carrots, potatoes, celery, onion, mushrooms and water chestnuts. Mix flour, sugar and salt; stir into meat mix.
Stir in tomatoes, Burgundy and bouillon.
Cover and bake for 4 hours.
Do not stir during cooking.

title: noodle dumps
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and mix until mealy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, until a soft ball of dough forms.
Roll dough on floured board 1/8-inch thick and cut into 1-inch wide strips.
Drop into boiling beef or chicken stock and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.
These will enhance any good homemade soup.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add oil; mix well.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat at medium speed 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured bread pan (loaf pan).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Let stand and cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: *Or any other assortment of vegetables.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Combine flour, Parmesan, salt, pepper and dill weed. Roll pork chops in mixture to cover well. Brown chops in electric skillet on both sides.
On top of them, spread the onions, sliced.

Add 1/3 cup water, cover and simmer on low 15 minutes. Add sliced, unpeeled zucchini and sprinkle the whole thing with leftover flour, to which you've added another 3 tablespoons Parmesan and 1/2 teaspoon paprika.
Don't stir it. Simmer it very slowly, covered, for about 25 minutes.

title: creamy rice and pineapple
directions: Cook rice in salted water until done. Drain water if there is much left.

Add 1 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla & pineapple to rice. Let cool. Combine cream cheese, remaining cup of sugar & remaining teaspoon of vanilla until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Add to cold rice mixture.

title: no-pot tomatoes
directions: Wash, core and cut each tomato into 8 chunks.
Peel the onions; chop them roughly and add to tomatoes.
Add butter or oil, salt, pepper and herbs.
Wrap the mixture in foil and seal the edges well.
(You may even want to wrap it in 2 layers.)
Tuck the package down in the coals or place it on the grill.
Depending on the heat of the fire, allow 15 to 30 minutes, enough time for the onions to get tender.
Serve these with grilled hamburgers, steak or chicken for an easy no-pot supper.

title: orange ham ring
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, orange juice, cracker crumbs and 1 teaspoon mustard; add to meat.
Mix well.
Spread evenly into jello ring mold.
Firmly pack meat.
Invert into shallow pan with sides.
Remove sides.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until done.
Spoon off fat.

title: pork chops and rice-a-roni
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown them in skillet.
Set aside.
Prepare rice-a-roni as directed on package, but use one can of chicken gumbo soup plus enough water to equal the water measurement on the box of Rice-A-Roni.
Do not cook.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Lay the browned pork chops on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottoms only of four 6-ounce custard cups, 8 large muffin cups, 3 x 1 1/4-inch or 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch. Beat egg in large bowl. Stir in milk and oil. Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate chips until flour is moistened. Fold in chocolate chips. Fill cups 3/4 full. Place custard cups on cookie sheet. Bake until golden brown. Custard cups approximately 25 minutes. Muffin cups approximately 20 minutes. Immediately remove from cups.

title: green bean pizza
directions: Spray an 8-inch skillet with cooking spray.
Layer ingredients in skillet; cover and simmer 20 minutes until all juices are evaporated.

title: fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine flour and paprika; set aside.
Combine egg and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in the egg mixture, then coat chicken in the flour mixture.
Heat oil in the skillet.
Place chicken in skillet and cook about 20 or 25 minutes.

title: pickled slaw
directions: Chop the first 6 ingredients.
Put in a large jar.
In a saucepan, put the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 minutes. Cool.
Pour over chopped vegetables.
Keep in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: ox roast soup
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Bring to a light boil. Add pastina, stirring often.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together well in a large airtight canister.
Use 1/4 cup of mix in a cup of boiling water to drink.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sweetener and peanut butter in mixing bowl. Mix in egg, milk and vanilla. Sift in flour, salt and baking powder; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheet. Flatten with hand or fork. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat pudding with milk.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: beef barbecue sauce or shredded barbecue beef
directions: Brown chopped onion in butter.
Add all ingredients.
Shred the beef before adding.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned caramel pie
directions: Brown 1 cup white sugar to a darkened color in an iron skillet. Do not burn, then set aside. Mix together 1 cup unbrowned sugar, egg, cornstarch and milk. Slowly add this mixture to browned sugar in the iron skillet and stir until mixture is thick and smooth. Pour in crust and top with meringue. Bake at 325° until golden brown. Makes 2 small pies or 1 large pie.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, cheese and sauce in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat some more.
Melt oleo and add to mixture.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Fold in apples.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar, when cooled, to dress it up.

title: weight watcher bran muffins
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large bowl.
Combine next six ingredients in medium-sized bowl.
Add flour mixture to cereal all at one time.
Microwave raisins in water to plump.
Mix in raisins.
Divide evenly into 12 muffin cups.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°, or bake in pan and cut in 12 equal parts.
Can be wrapped individually and frozen.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil all ingredients, except peaches, until sugar dissolves. Divide peaches into 2 quart-sized jars.
Slowly pour juice over peaches.
Heat lids for jars, place lids on jars and seal.
Let set for 2 to 3 days.

title: baked broccoli and shrimp
directions: Place drained broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine soup and cream cheese.
Add most of the shrimp and then pour over all the broccoli.
Sprinkle remaining shrimp on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream and vanilla pudding.
Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover Twinkies with Cool Whip mixture, then strawberries and pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: tasty hots
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Put 1 tsp. on each cracker and broil until lightly brown.
Serves 12.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and use graham cracker crumbs to make crust.
