Beat eggs, powdered sugar and remaining 2 sticks margarine for 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Place cut bananas on top of this.
Put pineapples (drained) on this.
Spread Cool Whip on top of this.
Then add nuts and garnish with cherries.

title: curd and onion chutney
directions: Slice onion and tomato.
Add yogurt and enough salt; mix well. Serve with the Biryani.
One small finely chopped chili may be added to this and mixed well.

title: baked squash
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with one package of the Fritos.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs together and then mix all together.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: slo-cooker spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and put in slo-cooker.
Add all of the other ingredients except the spaghetti.
Stir.
Cover and cook on high for 4 hours.
Stir in spaghetti noodles the last hour and stir occasionally.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir pumpkin into eggs.
Mix salt, flour, spices with sugar and stir into pumpkin.
Add milk gradually and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese noodle cake
directions: Cook noodles in 1 1/2-quarts salt water for 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain and place in a buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix together all ingredients and pour over noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.
Chill well before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, onion and pepper in baking dish; pour melted margarine over potatoes.
Layer cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with crushed corn flake crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 400°.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef and rice, forming into balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Combine soup and other ingredients in skillet and place meat balls in mixture.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour or a little longer.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup water.
Heat soup to boil.
Add the cream cheese and stir until dissolved. Add gelatine and mayonnaise.
Stir.
Mix all ingredients together in 6-cup mold. Chill overnight.

title: ribbon loaf
directions: Put Jell-O in separate bowls (dry).
Add 3/4 cup applesauce to each bowl.
Stir until blended well.
Place two double crackers end-to-end on rectangular platter.
Spread lime mixture (1/4 cup) on crackers.
Place new cracker layer on top.
Spread strawberry mixture (1/4 cup) on new cracker.
Repeat layers (fairly thin) until end with cracker on top.
Prepare topping following directions except omitting vanilla and adding sugar and extract before beating.
Top, then chill at least 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and oleo, then add flour.
Mix. Let cool.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Pour mixture into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Spread mixture on bottom of pan and a little up the sides.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Pastry will puff up like a cream puff.
Let cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter a medium casserole dish.
Place asparagus on the bottom. Mix together the green peas, mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese soup and pour over the asparagus.
Sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken
directions: Wash and dry fillets.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with first 3 ingredients.
Spread and blend.
Bake 1 hour at 250° to 275°.

title: peach-glow cold soup
directions: In blender container or bowl of food processor using metal chopping blade, place peach chunks, yogurt, orange juice and rind. Process until very smooth. Cover and chill.
Ladle into chilled bowls or short wide top wine glasses.
Top each with a slice of peach and a mint sprig.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: apricot cocktail
directions: Mix gin with the juice.
Fill the glasses in half with crushed ice and fill the other half with the mixture.
Decorate with cherries.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. Punch holes with fork all over cake. Mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan; heat until sugar dissolves, then pour over cake. Make pudding by package directions; when thick, pour over cake. Chill, then spread whipped topping over top and refrigerate.

title: 7-up salad(or can be used as a dessert)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 7-Up; pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish and chill slightly.
Add pineapple and bananas and let gel.
Beat the cream cheese into prepared Dream Whip until smooth; spread over Jell-O and chill.

title: fruity spice bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small mixing bowl, sift first 4 ingredients.
Add oats, stirring to combine; set aside.

title: chicken wings oriental
directions: Place wings in single layer of container and marinate overnight or several hours in sherry, soy sauce, ginger root, garlic and brown sugar (liquid to cover or almost).
Drain marinade and cook at boil for 6 to 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.

Place marinated wings in single layer in baking pan(s) and pour boiled marinade in to cover bottom of pan(s) to 1/2-inch. Bake for about 35 minutes, turning over wings or baste with additional liquid if necessary.
Test for doneness.
Should be golden brown.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternate adding milk and flour, beating at low speed.
Add vanilla last.
Put 3 Tbsp batter on griddle.
Cook only a few minutes.
Do not flip or turn. Make as many layers as you want. Cook layers on griddle on stove or thin layers in oven (best on top of stove).
If done in the oven, use 1/3 cup batter and bake in 325 degree oven for 10 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, chips and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto nonstick baking pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with sugar.

title: hobo beans
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in crock-pot 4 hours on medium or bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt kitty's apple cake
directions: Melt oleo or butter in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Pour in mixing bowl. Add sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Slice apples and put in bottom of pan.
Put batter on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or less.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Dream Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple juice.
Add defrosted strawberries and juice in separate bowl.
Let stand until partially set, then pour over cream cheese and chill.
If desired, chopped pecans can be added to pretzel crust.

title: easy turkey salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together soup and mayonnaise until smooth.
Fold in turkey, celery, red pepper, onions, parsley and pepper.
Serve mixture on leaf lettuce.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining salad mixture.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and drain. Season with salt and pepper. Add onions and mushrooms and cook until tender. Mix milk and flour. Add to meat mixture. Cook until thick. Serve over buttered noodles.

title: heavenly casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in small amount oil.
Mix next 5 ingredients well, then all remaining ingredients together.
Place in well oiled 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: strawberry foam punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl sugar, pineapple juice and lemonade.
Add ice cream (solid).
Pour ginger ale over ice cream. Stir lightly.
Serve at once.

title: grilled sesame chicken
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients.
Pour marinade over chicken. Cover and refrigerate for 4 to 8 hours.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Grate cabbage and pepper.
Add celery seed, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly; refrigerate.
Tastes best when made the day or several hours before serving.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes. Remove from stove. Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Beat until thick and spoon onto wax paper. Let them cool until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and water.
When thick add Cheez Whiz.
Combine sauce with broccoli.
Add eggs. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs using the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: posole
directions: Combine all, except the chili powder. Simmer 3 to 4 hours or until the meat is tender. Remove the bay leaves and garlic cloves. Add chili powder and simmer 20 more minutes. Serve with separate bowls of cabbage or lettuce, green onion, oregano, radishes and limes. Let each guest top the stew with their choice of condiments. Flavor is richest if stew is made a day ahead and reheated.

title: mrs. edith's festive chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool in broth.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into small chunks.
Cut celery, pickles and eggs into very small pieces.
Slice stuffed olives.
Mash pimento into smaller pieces, using a fork.
Combine all ingredients.
Add garlic powder and Accent.
Use enough Miracle Whip to moisten, usually 2 or 3 heaping tablespoonfuls.
Salt to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients, reserving a few bacon bits.
Roll into a ball.
Roll the cheese ball in the reserved bacon bits to coat it.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and put in a baking dish.
Just before baking, add milk and cornflakes.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°, or until heated through.

title: great pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water and let stand for 3 minutes, then add salt, sugar and egg.
Beat with fork until egg is combined with water and yeast.
Add flour and let dough stand for 5 minutes. Grease large cookie sheet or 2 pizza pans with plenty of oil. Spread dough on pans (for thicker crust, let dough rise 10 minutes).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Great with Ragu Garden Style sauce, Mozzarella cheese and other desired toppings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with sour cream, taco mix and Tabasco with mixer.
Spread mixture on dish.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Arrange pork chops in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with soup mix, rice and green pepper.
Spoon catsup over top.
Drizzle with Worcestershire sauce.
Pour water over all.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: mary's coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Then add next 7 ingredients.
Pour in buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle with topping (next 3 ingredients). Cover with chopped nuts and dot with 1/2 pound butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until top springs back.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt the butter in a large pan.
Add onions.
Cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Onions should become soft and have rich brown color.
Add the stock and bring it rapidly to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cut the bread into thin slices.
Spread with butter and toast under the broiler until crisp.
Arrange some of the toast on the bottom of an ovenproof soup tureen or bowl.
Sprinkle the toast with 1/2 the grated cheese.
Season with pepper.
Gently pour on the onion broth.
Float second layer of toast on the broth.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Place the bowl under broiler until cheese begins to bubble and brown.
Serve immediately. Serves 2.

title: a recipe for a home
directions: Mix thoroughly in a good natured pan.
Sprinkle a little sympathy evenly over the top.
Bake at any temperature for as long as you like.
And remember to serve large helpings and serve them often.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chuck roast in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 6 hours.
Shred meat with a fork and serve.
May be made ahead and frozen, adding water as necessary, when reheating.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings and remove tips, making 2 pieces (about 30 pieces). Deep-fry in pot or deep skillet, a few at a time, until crisp (about 8 to 12 minutes). Drain. Brush liberally with sauce.

title: crabmeat and corn bisque
directions: In saucepan, melt 1 stick butter.
Add flour and cook several minutes, stirring constantly.
Add hot chicken broth gradually and then add milk, cream and sherry.
In skillet, melt the other stick of butter.
Saute in the onions, green onions and parsley until soft.
Add to milk mixture, then add corn, crabmeat and season to taste.
Heat but do not bring to a boil.

title: summer stew
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and cook about 10 minutes. Add the last 2 ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: tuscan bean soup
directions: In a 5-quart heavy pan, saute in oil onions, carrots, celery, garlic and parsley about 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Add beans, turning over to coat well.
Add water and tomatoes, bouillon cubes and thyme.
Cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours until beans are soft.
At this point add salt if needed.
Take out about 1/3 of the beans and puree in blender.
Return to the soup. Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone and cut into pieces.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Layer bottom of dish with 1/3 stuffing. Add half of chicken.
Mix chicken soup with half of stock.
Pour over dish.
Spread 1/3 of stuffing and remaining chicken over this.
Mix celery soup and half of stock.
Pour over all.
Spread remaining stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tropical zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: roast beef(for crockpots)
directions: Add all ingredients to crock pot. Cook on low for 10 hours.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter bars
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until blended.
Stir in sugar, egg and vanilla, beating well.
Mix in flour mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line cookie sheet and sides with aluminum foil.
Place 40 soda crackers in pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on mixture and smooth out.
Put in refrigerator to sit.
Cut by crackers or break into pieces.

title: banana split delight
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla for 15 minutes (no less). Spread mixture evenly in graham cracker crust.
Spread sliced bananas over filling.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts and maraschino cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Stir ingredients together real good and pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: five flavors buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together 4 times.
Add flour and buttermilk alternating.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Cut top & center out of french bread.
Mix all ingredients together & stuff into bread. Then put top back on bread.
Cover tightly with tin foil & bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Slice while hot & serve.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes with onion, eggs, flour and salt.
Drop mixture from tablespoon into skillet containing hot fat.
Flatten each cake with back of spoon.
Fry to a deep golden brown on each side.
Makes about 8 pancakes.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour until well blended.
Add eggs and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Add margarine, coconut and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Sprinkle tops with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dutch honey
directions: Bring to a boil and add vanilla.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: egg puff
directions: Mix above ingredients on a large bowl. Pour into 9 X 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until eggs are set and top is light brown.

title: quick and easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add liquids and spices; bring to boil. Add beef base; stir well.
Add diced potatoes and vegetables. Simmer until tender (approximately 45 minutes).

title: boston brown bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, powder, soda and salt.
Stir in whole-wheat flour, corn meal and raisins; set aside.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Pour boiling water over this.
Add eggs. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to the mixture.
Stir well.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda. Refrigerate in covered dish for about 3 hours.
Roll out and let rise before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco and blend with hands until coarse.
Add enough cold water to make dough.
Pat out on floured cloth and cut out.
Makes about 20 to 22 biscuits.
Bake at 375° on sprayed pan until golden brown.

title: beer can chicken
directions: Remove and discard the neck, giblets and any excess fat from the chicken. Rinse the chicken, inside and out, under cold water and pat dry with paper towels. Lightly spray or brush all over with the vegetable oil and season, inside and out, with first 8 rub ingredients or your favorite barbecue rub.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of aluminum foil.
Pour soup mix over and add soup (undiluted).
Bring ends of foil together and lightly gather so juice cannot escape.
Cook in 325° oven for 2 hours.
Very good and easy to fix.

title: bud's pear preserves
directions: For each pound of fruit, use 3/4 to 1 pound sugar.
Peel a lemon; leave some white on it.
Slice thin.
(Use 2 cups of water.)
I don't use any, but let sugar stand on fruit overnight, to make it's own juice.
Put a layer of fruit, then a layer of sugar.
Do not cover; simmer for 2 hours or until fruit is tender. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: lenore's salmon patties
directions: Boil potato; peel and dice finely.
Break up salmon and remove skin and bones.
Add beaten egg, salt, pepper and diced potatoes to salmon.
Mix well and form into patties.
Coat with corn meal. Gently place into a skillet of heated oil and cook until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.

title: nutty buddy pies
directions: Cream
peanut butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add milk and
powdered sugar gradually. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into
3 graham
cracker crusts, plain or chocolate.
Sprinkle with peanuts
and drizzle with chocolate syrup.	Freeze until ready to serve.
Makes 3 pies.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; let cool.
Mix the dissolved Jell-O, cake mix, 4 eggs, lemon extract and oil together.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: arlene's burritos
directions: Pour refried beans in a saucepan with a couple of tablespoons of oil, 2 tablespoons of jalapeno juice and a few jalapeno pieces. Cook this mixture until bubbly.
Place all 8 flour shells on a cookie sheet.
Add in layers on the shells:
refried beans, tomatoes, black olives, a few jalapenos, and top with Cheddar cheese.
Fold by bringing up the bottoms of shells and folding the two sides over; hold in place with toothpick.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns or shells are crisp.
Good reheated in microwave.

title: pumpkin-cheesecake bars
directions: In large mixer bowl, on low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, oleo and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until light gray, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Red Layer:
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen berries and juice.
Stir until berries thaw, then chill until partially set.

title: "good" corn bread
directions: Add all dry ingredients; add eggs to milk and combine with dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening last.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Remove meat from pan and saute onion and celery in grease from sausage.
Put in casserole; add remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Stir a few times during baking.

title: crab strata
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Place a layer of noodles in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add a layer of crabmeat, then a layer of cottage cheese and half of the mushrooms.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour to make a paste.
Remove from heat and add milk and salt, stirring to blend.
Cook until smooth and thickened; stir in chives.
Pour half of sauce over casserole. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Cook the cake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Heat milk and sugar; beat eggs and add to creams.
Add vanilla; stir well.
Add Junket tablets that have dissolved; stir well.
Put in ice cream freezer and place paddle.
Do not disturb for 10 to 12 minutes, until it forms a custard, then freeze it. Makes 1 gallon.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and put into casserole to bake at 350° for 50 minutes
or
until
knife inserted in middle comes out clean. Can
be made ahead of time in refrigerator until ready to make.

title: south american coffee punch(50 servings)
directions: Add cinnamon sticks to coffee.
Let cool.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Add softened ice cream and vanilla to coffee.
Blend with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Float whipped cream on top. Sprinkle with fresh ground cinnamon.
Serve from punch bowl into tall glasses filled with crushed ice.

title: katrina's salsa
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
(Also used as dip for taco chips.) Makes about 2 cups.

title: mother's stacked green enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Combine soup, green chilies and beef.
Layer tortillas, beef mixture and cheese alternating layers (about 3 layers), ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: chicken taco pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Retain broth; remove bones and cut chicken into bite size. Combine chicken, enchilada sauce, mushroom soup, onion, garlic salt and pepper. Grease baking dish and line with Fritos. Add chicken mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Cover with Fritos. Pour 1 cup chicken broth over chicken mixture. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: southwest chicken & rice casserole
directions: Spread Texmati brown rice in greased 2 1/2 qt. casserole dish. Top with remaining ingredients, layering in the order given. *Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: city girl's cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use enough milk to make a medium-thin batter.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9-inch iron skillet, dusted with cornmeal.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: campfire (stovetop) pizza
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl, mixing well.
Press into skillet.
Layer with tomatoes and cheese.
Cook over medium heat (or campfire) until cooked through.

title: plain cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Use cookie press. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: walking salad
directions: Take off leaves of lettuce.
Spread peanut butter on individual pieces of lettuce.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Roll up; put toothpick in center to hold.
Serve cold.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a mixer bowl beat together cream cheese, butter or margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Spread over cooled cake. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and
salt
together
in
a large bowl. Mix margarine, cocoa and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to boil and add immediately
to dry ingredients.
Add sour cream, eggs and soda; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 x 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg; add butter. Pare and core apples; slice thin.
Make your favorite pie dough recipe; roll 1/4-inch thick and cut in 5-inch squares.
Sprinkle generously with additional sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and dot with butter.
Fold corners to center.
Pinch edges together.
Place 1-inch apart on greased baking pan.
Pour syrup over.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: peas salad
directions: Thaw peas, do not cook.
Combine with onion and celery.
Fold in sour cream and add bacon and nuts; chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
It's called Pig because it is so good, you make a pig of yourself eating it.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, mix all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 8.

title: rouladen - beef rolls
directions: Pound meat slices with steak mallet to 3 x 4-inch. Spread mustard thinly over meat. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, pickles, bacon and onions. Roll up; secure with skewers or string. Brown rolls in butter. Place seam side down in roaster with small amount of water. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Add sour cream before serving.

title: country breakfast
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Rip up the slices of bread and scatter them around the bottom of the pan.
Mix the milk and the eggs and pour over the bread, then pour on the soup.
Grate the cheese.
After putting your sausage on, sprinkle with cheese.

title: waldorf astoria red cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and set aside.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring; add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with flours mixed with salt.
Add vanilla. Combine baking soda and vinegar and add to batter.
Blend well. Turn into 2 lightly greased and floured 8 or 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly, then turn out on rack.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Beat until fluffy. Gradually add milk. Stir until blended.
Pour into crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing. Top with cherries. (Cherry Glaze.)

title: enchilada pie
directions: Saute onion and brown meat, add chili con carne, olives, tomato sauce and 2/3 3/4 cheese in greased casserole.
Put layers of tortillas and meat mixture and with layers of tortillas.
Sprinkle top with cheese and onions.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: mexican cheese squares
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Place mushrooms on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cut Feta cheese into tiny cubes and place in caps.
Heat bacon slowly until translucent and loses much of its fat.
Cut bacon into as many pieces as you have mushrooms.
Cover mushrooms with bacon and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese; blend in mayonnaise and lemon juice. Combine fruits, pecans and sugar.
Stir cream cheese and mayonnaise mixture into fruits.
Fold fruit mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into freezing tray.
Freeze in refrigerator freezing compartment.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Add the oil, flour, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well. Whip the egg whites and cream of tartar. Beat until very stiff peaks form.
Pour egg yolk mixture over stiffly beaten egg white mixture. Fold gently.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: braised chicken
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in 5-quart Dutch oven using fat. Remove chicken to bowl.
Add giblets to fat; brown well.
Spoon off all fat.
Add celery; cook 1 minute.
Stir in water, salt and pepper.
Return chicken to Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes.
Add beans; cook until tender.
To serve, debone chicken.
Cut into chunks.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook meat until it loses its red color and drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion and water.
Stir in sugar, garlic salt, oregano, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Combine macaroni and cottage cheese.

title: john's "cold slaw"
directions: Mix cabbage and onion together.
Blend the rest of the ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss until coated and chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
(These are a soft cookie.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix all together with a slotted spoon.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Punch holes all over top of cake while hot and put Topping over.

title: spicy roasted peanuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy skillet, cook oil, garlic and red pepper flakes over medium heat about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts and stir until well blended.
Pour peanut mixture onto a baking sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake to lightly browned.
Sprinkle paprika and chili powder over peanuts and stir.
Allow peanuts to cool completely. Yields 6 cups peanuts.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together; put in iron skillet.
Cover with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until middle is done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine cooked meat and mushroom soup in a saucepan.
Heat; do not boil.
Add sour cream and toss lightly.
Serve over cooked noodles or brown rice.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: basil french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth and garlic is minced. Chill in cruet or covered container.
Makes 1 2/3 cups dressing.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: beef and tomato and pepper sauce-guatemala(carne en jocon)
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan or casserole and saute the onion, garlic, and peppers until the onion is soft.
Add the meat and all the other ingredients except the tortillas.
The liquid should barely cover the meat.
Add a little more stock, if necessary.
Cover, and simmer gently until the beef is tender, about 2 hours.
If using tortillas soak them in cold water, squeeze them out, and crumble like breadcrumbs.
Add to the casserole and simmer, uncovered, until the sauce is thickened.
If using masa harina or cornmeal, mix it with a little cold water and stir into the stew, cooking just until the sauce is thickened (cornmeal will take a few minutes longer to thicken).
Serve the stew on a bed of Arroz Guatemalteco (rice, Guatemalan Style).

title: patti's brownies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs with a mixer. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a jelly roll pan which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(It is necessary to stir in part of the ingredients so as not to put too much air into the mixture.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients except graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Place on baking sheet.
Refrigerate 1 hour more.

title: oh and ah cake
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water with red food coloring and soda. Stir and set aside.
Cream together just until fluffy, sugar, shortening, eggs and salt.
Add alternately, by thirds, the flour and sour cream.
Add chocolate mixture and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix, chill and eat.

title: crab meat in tomato sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, bay leaf, oregano, thyme, pepper and celery. Cook until softened.
Add tomato or stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the crab meat and cook until the crab is fully warm.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in salty water for 10 minutes; drain and separate leaves.
Mix ingredients together.
Put in oven at 350° for 40 minutes; add thin slice of salt pork on top of each cabbage.
It will add taste and also keep the leaves from drying up.
Do not put too much salt, if using salt pork.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount of water until tender, about 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Place noodles in cake pan in layers of cottage cheese, Mozzarella and meat sauce between.
Repeat until all lasagna is used.
Put remaining cheese and meat sauce on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: almond brickle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: light 'n creamy macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 1-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
In a 1-quart saucepan, combine cheese spread and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking, until cheese melts.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in coconut.
Pour into a deep dish 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: shake and drop grits
directions: In a large
enough
pot,
fry
bacon crispy, add 2 cups cold water, stirring
in salt, add grits, then add enough cold water to barely
cover
grits.
Let	cook
slowly
until firm. Serve while hot.

title: strawberry fluff]
directions: Mix together.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: one meal chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in skillet; put in bottom of a flat pan.
Add onion, carrots and potatoes.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: veggie spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain. Keep warm. Saute garlic and onion in butter for 2 minutes. Add cauliflower, spinach, salt and pepper. Cook about 8 minutes, stirring until veggies are tender and crisp. Add cream. Heat to boiling. Stir in Parmesan cheese. Toss with spaghetti over medium heat until spaghetti is heated through. Serve at once.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Pop corn.
In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Boil together 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour over popped corn in large roaster pan.
Mix well.
Spread caramel corn on cookie sheets.
Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes. When cool, store.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and put on tray.
Mix next 3 ingredients for second layer.
Mix next ingredients for top layer. Cover with Cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes, sliced olives, green onions and finely chopped lettuce, if desired.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand overnight.
Rinse in cold water and drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack hot and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Beat 4 eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese and Ricotta. Gradually add eggs to cheese mixture.
Beat well.
Add flour and cornstarch to cheese mixture and beat well.
Stir in melted butter and vanilla; beat well.
Add sour cream with electric mixer.
Pour into ungreased spring-form pan and bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Increase heat to 375° and bake another 40 minutes.
Turn off heat and allow cake to cool in oven for 1 hour.
Remove and place in refrigerator until the next day.

title: cream of fresh tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan simmer tomato, onion, bay leaf, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper for 10 minutes.
Sieve and set aside (should be about 1 cup).
In same pan melt butter; stir in flour and the remaining salt.
Add milk all at once, cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly stir in hot tomato mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Dump sugar, buttermilk and oil in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and stir.
In a separate bowl, stir together eggs, vanilla, juice and nuts; add to main mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a greased tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Does not need frosting.)

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Blot drained vegetables dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle equal amounts of remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces. Discard ends.
Serve with spirals facing up.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: stir-fried bean sprouts
directions: Heat wok.
Add 2 tablespoons oil.
Stir-fry bean sprouts over high heat for 2 minutes.
Add salt; stir.
Stir-fry until thoroughly mixed for a minute.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fresh fruit.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade, condensed milk and Cool Whip by hand to consistency of mashed potatoes.
Add 3 cups well drained grated zucchini.
Pour into baked pie shell or individual sherbet glasses.
Refrigerate until set.
For St. Patrick's Day add green food coloring.
Yield 8 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Pat chicken with paper towels to dry.
Coat chicken with bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, in shallow pan. Bake for 35 minutes, uncovered, in a 425° oven.
Turn chicken pieces over and bake 30 minutes more.

title: almonds in a hay stack
directions: Mix ham, 4 ounces of cream cheese and 1/2 cup of salad dressing.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into a large cone shaped mound.
Combine 1/4 cup salad dressing and remaining cream cheese. Mix well and frost mound.
Cover with almonds and chill.
Serve with crackers or rye bread squares.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Precook vegetables almost done (the amount you need).

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Soak cornbread and bread crumbs in stock.
Saute onions and celery in butter until golden brown.
Combine crumbs and onion; mix with eggs and seasonings.
Add approximately 1 1/4 quarts stock to thoroughly moisten.
Mix well.
Stuff turkey.
If stuffing is baked in separate pan, bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: one dish meal
directions: Mix onion, celery, carrots, rice and chicken into greased casserole.
Put oil, water, broth and soup in a saucepan and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over casserole and mix gently.
Bake in a 350 oven for 1 hour.
*Or*
you can bake at 350 for 30 minutes, turn oven off and 2 1/2 - 3 hours later it will be warm and done. A tossed green salad is wonderful with this.

title: orange frosting
directions: Beat all until smooth.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 10 quarts.

title: jenny's chili
directions: Cook garlic in oil
until golden.
Crumble ground round in pieces and cook 10	minutes,
breaking
up to brown evenly. Pour off some of the
oil
and
drippings into another skillet and cook sliced onions and
green pepper until tender.
Add to cooked ground round
with tomatoes, beans, tomato paste, chili powder, cayenne pepper,
cloves,
bay
leaf,
salt and pepper. Cover; cook over low heat one hour.
If too dry add additional tomatoes.
If too
much
liquid,	uncover
and
simmer longer. Serve over rice (optional).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Line an 11 x 13-inch pan with foil; place chops in bottom of pan.
Scrub potatoes; slice over chops. Slice onions and separate into rings over potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cover giblets with water; boil until tender.
Remove from broth and cool.
Chop giblets, celery, onions and sausage.
Add to broth and cook until done.
Add more water if needed.
Crumble corn bread and bread crumbs.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and season to taste using salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add chopped parsley.
If mixture is too dry, add cream of chicken soup.
Stuff in turkey or bake separately in greased dish at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: drop pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; beat.
Add eggs; beat.
Add pumpkin. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mixing well each time. Add nuts; mix.
Add dates or raisins; mix well.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Frost with powdered sugar or Betty Crocker icing.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix together like pie crust; press into a 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate frosting bars
directions: Mix flour and sugar; work in butter to resemble corn meal. Add egg and vanilla.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread with chocolate chips while hot.

title: dump cake
directions: Using a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread cherry pie filling, then spread pineapple on top of that.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of pineapple.
Put pats of butter all over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut on top of butter, then put pecans on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove wrap and brown coconut for about 10 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Place noodles into large baking dish.
Mix together all ingredients; blend well.
Pour over noodles.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Garnish with jam or nuts.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa; stir in milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour batter into a 9-inch square baking pan.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Mix tomatoes, salt, ground pepper and onion; set aside.
Mix cracker crumbs with cheese.
Put half tomato mixture in greased casserole.
Top with half of crumb mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese finely.
Combine cheese, butter and flour with your hands until well mixed.
Form into 1-inch rolls.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Start baking at 375°, but lower to 350° and watch carefully as they burn.

title: yellow summer squash pie
directions: Beat egg well and add to grated squash.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add to squash.
Mix well.
Add milk and stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13 dish.
Break bread in small pieces.
Mix eggs and milk; beat together.
Pour over pieces of bread and sausage. Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Before baking, spoon mushroom soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kuchen
directions: Cut margarine into dry cake mix and add coconut.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Spread pie filling, sugar and spices over baked crust.
Mix sour cream and egg and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef; salt to taste.
Add green pepper and onion (optional) to suit your taste.
Use a 2-quart baking dish. Combine beef mixture with brown sugar and ketchup.
Last, add pork and beans.
Microwave (covered) on Medium-high for 10 to 12 minutes; stir halfway through cooking, or bake at 350° for 30 minutes until ingredients combine together.

title: yam casserole delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping (recipe follows) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herb shaker(replaces the salt shaker)
directions: Grind finely in blender and pour into shaker.
Enjoy.

title: katharine's fresh fruit tart
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and mix until thoroughly blended.
Whip the cream with an electric mixer and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon filling into crust and spread out evenly.
Heat jelly until melted.
Glaze the top with it using a pastry brush. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: mexican sausage dip
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix with melted cheese and tomatoes. Serve with nachos.

title: best ever old-fashioned spaghetti
directions: Saute hamburger, onion, green pepper and garlic in olive oil. Turn stove to simmer for 1/2 hour, frequently stirring.
In separate pan, boil noodles; strain. Serve sauce over noodles. Garnish with slice of warm garlic bread.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Add grated cheese, milk and uncooked macaroni.
Mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheap fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: You will need a 5-quart pot.

title: broccoli-cauliflower bake dish
directions: Melt together soups and cheese.
If using fresh vegetables, parboil until fork-tender.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: eggless cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the sugar, Crisco, salt and nutmeg. Add the milk and vanilla.

Mix thoroughly. Next, add 1 cup sifted flour to which baking powder and soda have been added. Beat thoroughly making a soft dough. Now add gradually 4 more cups sifted flour, beating well after addition.
Roll out on floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Bake in a 400° oven. Bake small cookies 6 minutes and large cookies 8 minutes. Frost and decorate as desired.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Place roast in large pan with enough cooking oil to cover bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides.
Add pepper flakes and flour to cooking oil; stir until brown.
Cover with tight lid and bake in 275° oven for 3 hours or until done.
Cut vegetables in quarters; add to roast the last hour of cooking.
When done, remove from oven; take out roast and vegetables.
Combine milk and water; add to brown mixture in pan. Stir until smooth over medium heat for a nice brown gravy.

title: pueblo stew
directions: In a 4 to 5-quart pan, cook onion, garlic and spices in oil until onion starts to brown. Add squash, hominy and tomatoes. Cook 5 minutes.

Add green and pinto beans, bouillon and water. Simmer uncovered until tender and consistency is that of thick stew (30 to 45 minutes). Add minced cilantro and ladle into bowls. Garnish with cilantro, sour cream and shredded Jack cheese.
Serve with tortillas.

title: cream soup basic
directions: Put all ingredients into container.
Cover.
Press button 14 for 30 seconds.
Stop motor and push down with spatula if necessary.
Blend longer if smoother consistency is desired.
Empty into saucepan and heat until hot, about 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Grease a casserole.
Layer green beans, chilies and cheese. Repeat.
Add milk and salt to beaten eggs; beat.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great with barbecued chicken and beef.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Wash and coarsely chop entire stalks of celery.
In bottom of Westinghouse electric roaster, spread celery, onions and tomatoes. Put pork butts on top and roast at 350° for 4 hours.

title: jello-lemon cake
directions: Take cake mix and bake according to directions.
Let cake cool.
Take a large fork and poke holes throughout cake.
Take jello (mix as directed) and pour over top of cake.
Take the lemon pie filling and spread over the cake.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: company koulourakia
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks and cream well. Add dissolved baking powder and baking soda, creaming well.
Add extracts and salt.
Remove from mixer.
Add flour by hand.
Your dough must be very soft.
Shape into S shape.

title: pam's banana pudding
directions: Mix the pudding mix with 5 cups milk. Stir in the condensed milk. Fold in the Cool Whip. Fold in the sliced bananas. Pour into 9 x 12 pan lined with vanilla wafers. Top with vanilla wafers. Chill before serving.

title: "mom's" boston baked beans
directions: In a big bowl, combine beans with 5 cups cold water and let soak all night.
In the morning, drain beans and reserve the water.
Put beans in fresh water (about 4 cups) and put to simmer for about an hour, covered.
Drain beans again and reserve water. In baking pot 1/2 salt pork and beans; shove rest in remaining beans, then mix together molasses, 1/2 bean water, paprika and onion and pour over beans.
Stir.
Bake pot covered at 300°.
You may add remaining water when needed, about 5 1/2 hours or until cooked.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and blend in sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back after touch.

title: grandmother pitts macaroni and beef
directions: Cook macaroni in large pan.
Add oil and onion.
When onion is tender or yellow in color, add tomatoes which have been mashed. Add salt and beef.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Then add macaroni and let simmer on low heat about 10 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Pull chicken off bone and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour in Veg-All, corn and mushrooms.
Mix soups and chicken broth in bowl and pour over into baking dish.
In bowl, mix melted butter, flour, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until crust is golden brown.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain fat.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Pour beef mixture in a lightly greased pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13x9 inch baking pan.
In a large bowl combine all ingredients for crust.
Mix well, mixture should be crumbly.
Press into baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Create filling and pour over hot crust.
Bake for 30 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool completely on a rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: baked black-eyed peas
directions: Chop the green bell pepper. Wash and remove any bad peas. Soak overnight.
Cook in same liquid.
Before cooking, add other ingredients. Cover completely with water. Bake in oven at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together. Roll out and cut with a glass.

title: alfred's chili
directions: Cut up bacon coarsely.
Slowly cook in large kettle until tender.
Chop onions.
Add to bacon and cook until translucent. Add meat and chili powder now.
Cook a while and mix well.
Add chopped mushrooms.
Drain tomatoes and add.
Now put in salt and beans.
Stir mixture.
Add sauce.
Stir again.
Cook on low for at least one hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Soften margarine and add sugar; beat until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well, then add water and corn meal and mix well. Pour into crust and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until firm in center.

title: holiday mix
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt chocolate and pour over mix. Spread mix in a single layer on wax paper.
Work quickly before chocolate sets.
When chocolate sets, break into pieces and store in airtight container.
Can be stored up to 2 weeks.

title: potato and spinach soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Pour off fat; add soup mix.
Gradually blend in water until smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Stir often; partially cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir now and then; add milk, spinach, nutmeg and bacon.
Heat and stir. Makes 3 to 4 servings.
tags: cream of potato dry soup mix

title: salmon cakes
directions: Debone salmon and remove skin coating.
Mash salmon.
Mix in beaten eggs and mashed potatoes.
Roll into oyster size oblong shape.
Roll in crushed crackers.
Fry quickly on both sides in fresh Crisco oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 12 to 13 large rolls.

title: german jagerschnitzel
directions: In a shallow dish, mix together the bread crumbs and flour. Season with salt and pepper. Place the egg on a separate dish. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Dip pork steaks in egg, then coat with bread crumb mixture. Fry in hot oil until browned on both sides, and cooked through, about 5 minutes per side. Remove pork to a platter and keep warm. Add onion and mushrooms to skillet and cook until lightly browned. Pour in water and dissolve bouillon cube. Simmer for about 20 minutes. Stir together the cornstarch and sour cream, stir into skillet. Cook over low heat until thickened, but do not boil. Spoon over cutlets and serve immediately. Best served with noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine and add flour and nuts.
Spread out evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange asparagus in 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inches).
Top with chicken.
Blend soup and milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 4.

title: pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza dough.
Mix tomato sauce, onions and green peppers together.
Spread on pizza crust. Sprinkle hamburger, sausage, pepperoni, ham and bacon.
Sprinkle cheese on last.
Put in oven until cheese has melted.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown beef and garlic.
Drain; mix next 4 ingredients in bowl. Stir in beef.
Fill shells.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: lobster casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Cut lobster in pieces and mix into cracker crumbs.
Stir melted butter into mixture.
Lightly salt and pepper.
Just before putting in oven, pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover for 20 minutes.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-sized pieces. This will take about 2 months, so start early.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook four weeks at 485° or until you run out of fuel.
If lots of people are expected, add the 2 rabbits; but do this only if necessary.
Some people don't like to find hare in their stew. This serves about 5000.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line a muffin pan with paper baking cups. Beat milk, oil and egg.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt all at once until flour is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Fold in blueberries; fill baking cups.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.

title: take 2 turkey
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour while stirring with a wooden spoon.
Stir until smooth and slowly add milk.
Stir with wire whisk and add salt and pepper.
Add turkey, peas and pimentos.
Continue to stir with wooden spoon over low heat until sauce is thickened and turkey is heated.
Serve over biscuits or toast.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 9-inch round or 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Mix well. Spread pecans evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.

title: pork roast
directions: Slice the pork skin with sharp knife in thin slices through the fat.
Salt all sides of pork.
Cook at 325° for 40 minutes per pound.
During cooking, pour cold water over roast several times. When finished cooking, before removing from oven, turn temperature up to 400° to brown the rind; this will also make it crisp.
Save all the juice and drippings for the gravy.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and brown sugar, mixing well.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir in sugar, vanilla and almond chips.
Cover and chill up to 8 hours.
Serve dip with apple or pear wedges.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar in heavy iron frying pan over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until all lumps are gone and sugar is a rich, golden color.
Remove from fire; add butter and pour over nuts which have been spread in a shallow, well-greased pan.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: fat pork cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar; add beaten eggs and all dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 250° about 3 hours.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crush the Oreos in food processor; save 2 cups for the top. Melt the oleo; mix with cookies.
Press in pan or casserole. Chill.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 6 ounces Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Combine the pudding with the milk.
Pour over top the 6 ounces Cool Whip.
Put crumbs on top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together real well.
Add the eggs; beat. Dissolve the soda in the applesauce.
Add flour, spices, raisins and floured nuts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter in large bowl with electric mixer. Add egg and molasses. Mix well. Place dry ingredients in large bowl. Blend with whisk. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Mix by hand. Roll out on well floured surface to less than 1/4-inch thick. Bake on sprayed cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool. Decorate as desired. (Tie red bows around their necks.)

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and milk alternately until sugar is melted.
Add vanilla until blended, then gently fold in chopped nuts.

title: autumn stew
directions: Saute meat in a little butter until brown and put it in an 8-quart kettle.
Saute onions, garlic and green peppers and combine with meat.
Mix in all other ingredients, except pumpkin; cover and simmer for one hour (or until meat is tender).
Mix cornstarch with a little pan liquid and blend into sauce.
Cut the top off the pumpkin, remove seeds and membranes and fill pumpkin with stew.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Place pumpkin on large platter (carefully) and serve from it.
Serves about 12.

title: arizona casserole
directions: In large heavy skillet, brown beef in batches. Saute onions and garlic with last batch of meat. Return all meat to pan. Sprinkle chili powder over meat and mix well. Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, 1/2 can of olives and green chilis. Simmer 15 minutes. Beat cottage cheese and egg and set aside. Spread 1/3 meat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with 1/4 lb. Jack cheese, half of cottage cheese mix and 1/2 tortillas. Repeat. Finish with meat layer. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Garnish with remainder of olives, green onions and sour cream.

title: caramelitas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, butter, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Blend until crumbly.
Reserve half of the crumb mixture. Press remaining crumb mixture in prepared pan and bake 10 minutes. Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of crust. Stir flour into caramel topping.
Drizzle over chips and nuts. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture and bake 15 minutes. Cool 1 to 2 hours before cutting.
Refrigerate.
May double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen bars.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Layer casseroles.
Start with crushed crackers, then oysters, then salt and pepper and 2 teaspoons of margarine.
Start all over until you are to the top of dish.
Cover with milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Stir in sifted flour and salt.
Beat egg white and fold into mixture.
Add pecans and finely chopped fruit.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix onion, butter, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on both sides of rolls that have been sliced in half.
Cover one side with ham, layer cheese over ham and close buns.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted.
The rolls aren't separated until ready to serve.
Canned ham or thick sandwich ham chopped fine is excellent.

title: strawberry pretzel delight
directions: Mix pretzels, brown sugar and melted margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add strawberries.
Let cool until slightly thickened.
Cream sugar and cream cheese; fold in whipped topping. Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Pour gelatin mixture over that; refrigerate (does not store well over 3 days as pretzels absorb moisture).

title: chick n' chiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine onion, pepper and oil. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes until veggies are tender. Remove from heat. Add chicken, 1/2 cup cheese and chilies to veggies; set aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, mix all together and freeze.

title: aunt edna's potatoes
directions: Put frozen potatoes in lasagna-type casserole.
Add diced onion.
Drizzle 1/2 of the melted margarine on top.
In separate bowl, mix chicken soup and sour cream. Add to potatoes and stir. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put corn flakes on top of cheese and drizzle remaining melted margarine on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Cut into pieces.
Mix chicken, soup and broth.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix butter and stuffing; spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: warehouse salad dressing
directions: Blend and refrigerate in a closed jar.

title: chocolate ice cream brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions and let cool in pan.
Spread ice cream over brownies and let freeze until firm. Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to medium and cook 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Cool.
Spread over ice cream. Freeze.
Remove 5 minutes before serving and cut into squares.

title: pow!
directions: Heat all ingredients to simmering.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on package and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (according to directions).
While still warm, poke holes 1 inch apart with the end of a wooden spoon.
Let cool.
Pour sweetened condensed milk into holes and spread caramel (or butterscotch) topping on top of cake.
Refrigerate until completely cooled.

title: fortune's tators
directions: Boil potatoes; mash boiled potatoes.
Add butter, salt and cream. Whip.
Garnish with cheese slices.
Microwave for 1 minute. Serves 3 (or one large 6 year old).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms, removing stems (save for soup or spaghetti sauce).
Drain, wash and shred crabmeat.
Fix Stove Top stuffing per box directions.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except for chips. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Top with crushed chips. Bake 15 minutes at 425° or until bubbly and browned.

title: baked custard
directions: Scald milk. Beat egg until well blended and pour over it very gradually the milk. Add sugar and nutmeg. Strain into custard cups. Set filled cups in a pan of hot water until firm. Test with knife; if it comes out clean, custard is done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased glass baking dish for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly and golden brown.
Best served with dip size Fritos.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: unusual salad
directions: Arrange in layers as listed. Spread mayonnaise over top and seal to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise. Let stand 8 hours.
Before serving, toss and mix mayonnaise. Top with bacon, eggs and sprinkle with cheese. Serves 12 to 14.

title: pork seasoning sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until butter melts.
Pour into spray bottle.
Spray on pork chops or pork patties as they are being grilled or broiled.
This is the official Mid-Ohio Chemical recipe.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and Equal with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Place 2 cups milk in mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Add the remaining Cool Whip, salt and lemon extract; stir until well blended.
Let stand about 3 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese layer; refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Garnish with Cool Whip when served.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, cornstarch and sugar and then add cold water.
Mix well and cook over medium heat.
Keep stirring until thickened and clear.
This is the glaze.
Cool until lukewarm and pour 1/2 into cooked pie crust.
Add sliced strawberries and pour remaining 1/2 glaze on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: chicken stuffed filo(origin: greek)
directions: Pan broil the broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and celery. Lightly saute in 1/4 pound butter (oleo) all vegetables, adding zucchini.
Season to taste.
Allow to cool to room temperature. Add cottage cheese, Feta and chicken pieces.
Blend carefully. Season to taste.

title: eclair cake made lite
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Beat in Cool Whip.
Spread a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish, a layer of pudding, a layer of graham crackers and ending with graham crackers on top.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together shape in loaf pan.
Put melted butter on top to help brown.
Bake 350 for about 1 hour.
Can be made into patties- roll in cracker crumbs, fry in hot shortening.
Just enough to keep them from sticking.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with a wire whisk or hand beater until smooth.
Makes about 18 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: duck stew ala brick olletto
directions: You will also need a second hand brick (cleaned).

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Place in small saucepan the first three ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over combined sugar and flour.
Add slightly beaten eggs, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake in oblong pan 9 x 13-inch at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Drain peaches and line peaches in crust.
Mix sugar, eggs, butter, flour and salt.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add yogurt, poppy seed, orange juice and peel and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well. Pour batter into floured 1-quart mold.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool completely, then dust with powdered sugar and sprinkle with poppy seed.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, oil, eggs and water. Beat 2 minutes. Stir in chips with spoon. Place in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°. Cool in pan 20 minutes. Turn out. Cool completely. Use favorite icing or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix jello (dry) and sugar; pour over rhubarb that is in baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Pour water over cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, granulated sugar and water in saucepan and cook over low heat until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add nuts and cool.

title: frozen peanut butter pie(ingredients for 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine chocolate crumbs and sugar.
In small saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter over low heat. Stir into crumbs until well blended.
Press into bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: coffee toffee balls
directions: Combine
granulated
sugar and packed brown sugar, corn syrup, light
cream,
butter, milk, coffee and salt in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook
over
moderate
heat,
stirring often, until sugars
dissolve
and butter melts.
Lower heat.
Cook, stirring occasionally,
until
candy
reaches 240° on a candy thermometer. Continue cooking, stirring constantly so mixture doesn't burn, until candy reaches 246° (a bit dropped in cold water will
form a firm ball).
Remove from heat immediately; let stand 2 minutes. Stir in vanilla.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Spray 3-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Put layer of potatoes, beans, onions, hamburger (do not cook) and repeat layers.
Mix one can water with tomato soup and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: steak supper
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place a piece of foil in bottom of baking dish.
Place meat on foil.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion mix.
Pour over top of meat.
Top with vegetables; sprinkle with water.
Fold foil and seal.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Save 2 tablespoons of grease or use oleo to saute chopped onion.
In a pot, bring 6 to 7 cups of water to boil.
Dissolve bouillon and thicken with cornstarch.
In six individual, ovensafe, 1-cup soup bowls, crumble toast, then bacon and top with half of the Swiss cheese.
Pour liquid bouillon over dry ingredients and top with remaining half of cheese.
Broil soups until cheese is melted on top.
Serves 6.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening until red disappears; drain drippings.
Add onions, peppers, tomatoes, ketchup and sauce. Cook until onions and peppers are fairly tender.
Season to taste. Combine meat mixture with macaroni; pour into casserole dish. Spoon soup over it; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole dish. Top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dick's delicacy
directions: Sauce:
Combine catsup, horseradish, Tabasco sauce and lemon juice in a bowl.

title: peanut butter pie supreme
directions: In bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in peanut butter, then milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust. Cool.

title: whipping cream lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, beat butter with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until well combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition, just until egg is absorbed. Stir flour into batter alternately with cream, beating after each addition.
Mix in lemon extract and grated lemon rind.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake one hour and 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add onion and pepper; cook to soften; add salsa.
Heat through; remove from heat.
Cut up cream cheese; add to mixture.
Stir until blended through.
Pour into baking dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Serve hot with Triscuit crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in order and one at a time.
(The mixture will be extremely thick.)
Place in a greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and turn onto a plate.
Top it off with a little Cool Whip.

title: lime salad
directions: Combine jello, water and cheese.
Combine milk and mayonnaise. Add to jello mixture, then add pineapple and pecans.

title: hillbilly salad
directions: Cook cornmeal mix.
Layer in a bowl.
Place bacon crumbs on top of layers.
In a separate bowl, pour pickle juice with salad dressing.
Put 4 or 5 bags of Sweet 'N Low in and beat until smooth.
Pour over top.
Poke holes, then toss without stirring. Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix together the butter, onion, milk, chicken soup, cheese and rice.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add cooked broccoli. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix dressing and butter, place half the dressing in ovenproof baking dish.
Combine the next 7 ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Top with remaining dressing and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: peach custard ice cream
directions: Scald both milks.
Beat eggs; combine with half of the sugar. Mix flour and salt with remainder of sugar.
Blend all with hot milk; cook until it thickens.
Add mashed peaches and vanilla; freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter, mix remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: tupperware bread
directions: Use Tupperware Fix 'N Mix bowl.
Mix ingredients together. Seal.
Let rise for approximately 30 minutes (seal should pop). Butter hands and separate into 3 loaves.
Let rise in pan 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb.
Let stand while mixing batter. Mix all together thoroughly.
Add sugared rhubarb and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pans and sprinkle with topping.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute nuts in butter and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients in baking dish and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Thoroughly cook ground sausage until brown.
Remove stems from mushrooms and mince.
Saute stems and onion in butter.
Add sausage, parsley, bread crumbs, cheese, lemon juice and salt. Fill caps with mixture and place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then broil 3 minutes until delicately browned.

title: turkey mushroom bake
directions: Rinse wings, place in pot of water and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove skin and debone turkey.
Combine stuffing crumbs and 1 stick of melted butter.
Saute mushrooms, onion and celery in 1 stick of melted butter.
Combine soup and sour cream.
In a greased 2 quart baking dish, layer in the following order:
1/2 the crumbs, turkey, mushroom mix, soup and sour cream mix, cheese and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jubilee salad mold
directions: Drain raspberries, reserving syrup.
In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sherry, lemon juice and reserved raspberry syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in raspberries and cherries.
Pour into a 5 or 6 cup ring mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce lined platter if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: bubble cake
directions: Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients, except margarine.
Put in bag and shake biscuit pieces in this. Place coated pieces in greased tube pan.
Mix margarine with leftover sugar mixture and spoon over biscuit pieces in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carolyn's salad dressing
directions: Put ingredients in quart jar and shake well.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: caramel dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Serve with your favorite fruit.
Great on apples.

title: creamy crock-pot potatoes
directions: Toss potato slices in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Drain and put half of potatoes in greased crock-pot.
Top with half the onion slices, flour, salt and pepper.
Add remaining sliced potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with remaining flour, salt and pepper.
Add butter and undiluted soup.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Combine the cream cheese and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add to chicken mixture, stirring well.
Cover and chill.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender, about 2 to 3 hours.
Discard broth. Cool chicken, then tear chicken into bite-size pieces (discard bones and skin).

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together concentrated lemonade, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Pour into pie crust.
Freeze until the pie is hard.
Serve frozen.

title: baked squashthe black-eyed pea's
directions: Cut each squash into 3 or 4 pieces.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain in colander and mash.
Combine with other ingredients.
Pour into a 3 quart casserole that has been lightly greased or sprayed with non-stick vegetable spray.
Cover with a light layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cheddar cheese loaves
directions: In a
large
bowl,
dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1 cup flour, sugar,
salt, soda, sour cream and egg.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed
in mixer.
Stir in remaining flour and cheese. Pour into greased
loaf
pan.
Let
rise 50 minutes in a warm place.
Batter will rise slightly, not double.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at
350° until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: six layer dinner
directions: In a
large
casserole
dish place potato slices, onion slices and tomatoes.
Spread hamburger over tomatoes.
Sprinkle rice over all and lay bacon on top of rice.

title: daisy's mountain cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, apples, nuts, coconut, carrots and vanilla. Beat all together.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Sprinkle chicken with Greek seasoning and garlic powder.
Salt as desired.
Mix together mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Brush this on chicken breasts (a little thick).
Roll coated chicken in a mixture of crushed Post Toasties and Parmesan cheese.
Spray pan with Pam.
Arrange chicken in prepared pan.
Bake in 300° to 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
