Remove from oven and drizzle a little butter on top.
Return to oven and bake until golden brown.

title: apple harvest pudding
directions: In medium bowl cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices and add to sugar and egg mixture, alternating with 1 cup milk.
Mix until moistened, then add the remaining fruits and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be iced when cool or served with whipped cream or ice cream.
A thin cream cheese icing is good on this, and freezes well.
Serves 15.

title: fruit delight
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar and cream of tartar and beat until foamy.
Crush saltines.
Add vanilla, saltines and pecans.
I put in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip, then fruit on top and refrigerate. Delicious.

title: mild spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil until soft.
Add ground beef and seasoning.
Stir until meat loses pink color.
Stir in Worcestershire and tomatoes.
Mix thoroughly; add rice.
Yields 5 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well, then add the oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
Divide dough in half.
On waxed paper, form each half into a roll.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: shrimp crackers
directions: Mix shrimp, mayonnaise, sour cream and onion.
Spread on Triscuits or wheat crackers and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: In greased casserole, put 1 can of beans; mix sugar and mustard together and sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over beans.
Repeat with second can of beans and mixture.
Place bacon over top and spread with catsup.
Bake uncovered for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: apple tortillas
directions: Divide pie filling between the tortillas and roll up.
Spray baking dish with Pam and place filled tortillas in dish.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Mix eggs and vanilla; add in baking powder and soda.
Add flour.
Roll out to 1/4-inch in thickness. Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. Cool and ice.

title: nut tocies
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into balls the size of hickory nuts. Place into each
cup
of
a small-size muffin pan.	Fit into cups with your fingers.

title: roasted pepper and artichoke tapenade
directions: Combine all ingredients in processor. Process using on/off turns until mixture is well blended and finely chopped. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve on crackers or toasted bread.

title: mom's cheese pie
directions: In a mixer bowl blend sour cream and cream cheese until smooth. Beat in eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour into prepared 9 inch graham cracker crust. Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on rack.

title: shrimp and scallop carey
directions: Heat clarified butter or oil in large saute pan.
Lightly flour shrimp and scallops and place in hot pan.
Cook two minutes and turn over.
Add artichoke hearts, leeks and mushrooms.
Cook one minute.
Add white wine, lemon juice.
Cook until shrimp and scallops are solid white, approximately two more minutes.
Finish with raw butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or linguini.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix; put in dish and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° (9 x 13-inch dish).
Cool.

title: champagne punch
directions: Makes about 45 (4 ounce) servings.
Pretty with an ice ring.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll by spoonfuls in coconut.

title: rhubarb cake mix
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half the batter into a greased, oblong pan.
Add rhubarb slices, sprinkle sugar over fruit and add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve with whipped cream.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Combine pimento strips, vinegar, sugar, paprika, salt, and water and blend well to make a marinade.
Mix all ingredients together and marinate 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: microwave chewy granola bars
directions: Grease 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cream brown sugar, sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add honey, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Gradually blend in flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt at low speed.
Stir in rolled oats, rice cereal, almonds, chocolate chips or raisins and wheat germ.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Sprinkle dried onion rings on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sweet milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth. Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork and bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown at 350°.
Can be topped with a candy kiss to add a chocolate flavor.

title: grits baked
directions: Cook grits in chicken broth. Melt butter in hot grits; add eggs, cheese, salsa (or Ro-Tel tomatoes), onions and garlic. Add grits cooked in chicken broth and beat lightly. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 250°.

title: baked scrod fillets
directions: Dip fish in salad dressing. Place in single layer, skin side down, on buttered 15 x 10 baking dish.

title: betty lyken's pie crust for freezing
directions: Makes 6 double pie crusts.

title: ham and potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Combine other ingredients.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large electric mixer bowl; beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Turn on wire rack to cool. Frost with Pistachio Frosting.

title: cheese cake
directions: Scald the water and milk. Let cool. Add the yeast and sugar. Set aside.

title: orange cheese ball
directions: In food processor, grate the cheese, then add the rest of the ingredients. Will form a ball.
Put on plate and decorate with strips of green peppers.

title: sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Heat to 125°. Beat in egg.
Mix yeast with about 2 cups of flour.
Add to milk mixture and beat well.
Add rest of flour.
Knead dough until elastic.
Let rise until dough is double.
Roll out and make into cinnamon rolls.
Place rolls in pan on top of the butter and brown sugar mixture.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rolls rise. Bake about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Immediately invert when taken out of oven.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with egg white frosting.
Put in oven and brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli corn bread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lagoon chicken salad
directions: Gently toss together chicken, wild rice, grapes, apple, celery, 1/2 cup of slivered almonds and the water chestnuts.

title: grilled vegetables(serves 6)
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients in a large bowl. Set aside. Cut carrots and next 5 ingredients into large pieces. Add to vinegar mixture. Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain vegetables. Arrange vegetables evenly in a grill basket. Grill, covered with grill lid, over medium-high heat (350° to 400°) for 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp-tender, turning occasionally. If desired, bake vegetables in a 400° oven, using all the juices for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: green beans with cream cheese sauce
directions: Cook beans with 1/2 teaspoon salt according to package directions.
Heat mushrooms in margarine a few minutes.
Blend milk into softened cream cheese with celery seed and salt.
Spoon cheese sauce over drained green beans, garnish with mushrooms. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and eggs thoroughly. Mix rest of ingredients; stir.
Chill dough.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Melt butter and add cocoa and cola. Heat to boiling and cool slightly.
Pour over flour mixture and stir.
Add other ingredients, except the marshmallows; after mixing well, add them.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2 5/8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost in pan while still hot.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place meatballs in a baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skinny soup
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Simmer slowly until vegetables are tender.
Contains 46 calories/cup and 0 fat.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Put 2 cups milk in bowl. Mix in pudding mix, then add Cool Whip. Put layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Put 1/2 pudding mixture on top, then graham crackers, then rest of pudding, then crackers again. Heat tub of frosting in microwave until thin. Pour over last layer. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Best if overnight. Cut and eat.

title: corn bread or corn pone
directions: Put dry ingredients in pot. Add hot water first, then remaining ingredients. Cook on top of stove until slightly thinned.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch aluminum pan. Cook at 350° until brown.

title: taco biscuit pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Arrange 7 biscuits around the side of pie plate and three in the bottom of ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Press biscuits to form crust.

title: 1 minute chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Cool partially, then beat.

title: skillet burger sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and celery.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Spoon into hamburger buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt, eggs, butter and flour.
Then alternately add soda and milk.
Chop walnuts and bananas; blend well.
Turn into a greased bread tin.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Toss first 7 ingredients well together.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat these ingredients together.
Add apples and nuts. Add egg mixture and apple and nuts to flour mixture.
Will be stiff and heavy.
I use my hands to pat it in a greased loaf pan, 9 x 12-inch pan or close.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Drain apple slices and place in greased 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle apples with cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice, then pour in 1/4 cup water.
Cream together flour, sugar and butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot, topped with heavy cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Pour off fat.
Cook noodles and rice in water for 7 minutes.
Put all in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift 4 cups flour into mixing bowl.
Make hole in flour.
Mix all dry ingredients with other cup of flour and sift into hole. Pour buttermilk, oil and yeast into hole and start mixing.
Cover and let set in refrigerator at least 3 hours.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: super easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Cake:
Stir cake mix, cherry filling, eggs and vanilla; put in greased 9 x 13-inch or jelly roll size pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: brandy's tuna surprise
directions: Add all 3 ingredients to a saucepan and heat.
Serve poured over homemade biscuits or baked refrigerator biscuits.

title: diabetic salad
directions: Thaw juice.
Put in blender.
Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and add to juice.
Add boiling water; start blender.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Make day before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, enough to cover the bottom half of your baking dish.
Cover the potatoes with the chopped onion and pieces of butter.
Add salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, mix the sour cream and soup.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of casserole and bake (covered) for one hour.
Bake uncovered for the last 5-10 minutes.

title: sauteed mustard greens
directions: In a large saute pan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until onions begin to turn brown and caramelize, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add mustard greens and briefly cook until mustard is wilted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix peaches and sugar in a blender. Add to other ingredients. Put in ice cream freezer. Churn until frozen.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: indian curry
directions: Brown 1/2 cup onion.
Add spices and water.
Add choice of meat; cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add cubed potatoes. Serve with rice and top with chutney.
May add 1 can tomatoes, chopped green onions, salt and pepper to taste.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Melt butter; pour over bread crumbs. Spread sausage over crumbs.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Pour over sausage and egg mixture.
Chill in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Bring to boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Line 13 x 9-inch buttered dish with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour this mixture over lined crackers in dish.
Layer this with graham crackers, ending with crackers.
Pour chocolate mixture over top layer of crackers.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: ham glaze
directions: Score the ham and put a clove in the center of each scoring. Mix brown sugar, lemon juice and dry mustard to a paste consistency.
Spread mixture on top of ham.
Bake at 325°.
Baste often.
When drippings are brown, add ginger ale and sherry.

title: grilled swordfish on a bed of wilted chard
directions: Marinating the swordfish in a mixture of yogurt, olive oil and lemon juice for 20 minutes will ensure a protective coating that will crisp the outside of the fish while retaining the flavorful juices.
Quickly wilted greens are a nice foil for the tender fish.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed and drain. Brown beef, onion, cilantro, green pepper and red chilies.
Drain well.
Mix raw egg in Ricotta cheese.
(Will keep cheese from becoming runny.)
Layer all ingredients with the topping being the Monterey Jack and black olives.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix taco seasoning mix with hamburger; set aside.
Combine softened cream cheese, sour cream and 2 tablespoons of salsa.
Spread on large tray or cookie sheet.
Layer remaining ingredients in this order:
hamburger, lettuce, onions, tomatoes, remaining salsa and shredded cheese.
Use Tostitos or plain nacho chips to dip with.

title: savory potato gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet until soft and transparent.
In a shallow baking dish, arrange in layers sliced potatoes and onions, sprinkling with garlic and seasonings in between layers for best flavoring.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Add whipping cream all over top.
Sprinkle with paprika if used.
Increase oven to 400° and bake for another 10 to 20 minutes until potatoes are soft and fork tender and gratin slightly browned on top.

title: moravian mints
directions: Put confectioners sugar in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Add water; allow to dissolve.
Add flavoring.
When mixture hardens sightly on top, drop on waxed paper about 1-inch in diameter.
Color can be added as desired.

title: granny's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour into melted butter in baking dish.
Spoon fruit in baking dish throughout batter.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: raisin sauce(serves 8)
directions: Put raisins in cold water; slowly bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Melt butter; add dry ingredients and blend thoroughly. Add raisins and liquid.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add lemon juice.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Cut each breast in half, wrap each in slice of bacon.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and layer with chipped beef.
Place bacon wrapped breasts on top of chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 275°. Uncover and bake 1 to 2 hours more.

title: bud's famous salmon loaf
directions: "Clean" salmon.
Mix salmon together with all other ingredients.
Mixture will be soupy.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat very thoroughly.
Alternate dry ingredients: flour, baking powder and baking soda with the sour cream and vanilla.
Before baking, place cinnamon, raisins and brown sugar mixture on top.
Stir it through with a knife to blend.
Mixture will be very thick.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Put in a large bowl; mix thoroughly and refrigerate overnight. Great at holidays!

title: poster paint
directions: Combine cornstarch with 3/4 cup cold water.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Stir hot water into cornstarch mixture.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils clear.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin mixture and soap flakes or detergent.
Put in jars for different colors.
Add color by using either food coloring, all-purpose dye or tempera paint.

title: warm chipped beef dip
directions: Put in pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: fig preserves
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water; place figs in a large kettle, then pour soda water mixture over the figs. If soda water does not cover figs, add enough water to cover. Soak for 10 minutes. Drain and rinse figs with fresh water. Add 3 cups of sugar, poured over top of the fruit.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter.
Stir in box cake mix with 1 egg.
Press in 9 x 13 pan or baking dish for crust.
In bowl mix: 2 eggs, 8 ounces of cream cheese, and 1 box powdered sugar.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Combine coconut and pecans; spread on bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan that has been greased and floured. Mix box of cake mix according to pkg. directions; pour into pan. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, and butter. Drop by teaspoonfuls over top of cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together, roll by hand into small balls, chill for 1 hour.
Stick with toothpick.
Melt paraffin with chocolate, keep warm.
Dip each ball into chocolate dip and allow to cool.

title: spinach pie
directions: Combine spinach with cheeses, onion, eggs, oil, salt, pepper and dill.
Arrange 8 phyllo and brush with butter in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cover with spinach filling.
Cover top with 8 more buttered phyllo.
Seal top layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix everything together and chill overnight.
Add 1 or 2 cups of marshmallows before serving.

title: caramel dip
directions: Combine and use as dip for apples.

title: cookies and  cream pie
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
let stand 5 minutes.

title: peggy's fruit cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put ingredients in layers as listed, pouring water and butter over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: tomatoes and onion salad
directions: Place tomato slices in a deep bowl and sprinkle with onions and basil.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour over tomatoes.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 3 hours.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean as for custard pie.

title: glogg
directions: Warm up and serve hot.
(Can be reheated, but do not boil.)

title: shrimp and cheese delight
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces.
Melt over hot water.
Gradually stir in milk, beating until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour half of the cheese sauce into greased casserole.
Place half of rice over sauce.
Cover with shrimp, then remaining rice, then remaining cheese sauce.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add melted margarine and eggs.
Knead and shape in rolls.
Roll in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: brownie bake cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, sugar and water; mix well. Add eggs one at a time using electric mixer. Stir in sour cream and chocolate chips by hand.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter well add sugar gradually and beat well.
Add jam and coffee, to which spices have been added.
Beat yolks of eggs and blend with first mixture.
Sift flour and add alternately with sour cream, in which soda has been dissolved.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers in moderate oven at 350° for 55 minutes.
Ice cake in cream cheese or strawberry icing.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream sugar
and
butter
in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in
eggs, one at a time.
Blend in bananas.
Add mixture of dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour
into
greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in two tablespoons of margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown round steak in skillet. Add soup mix and can of mushrooms with liquid. Heat until bubbly. Slowly add sour cream and cook until
heated. Serve with noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: graham bars
directions: Line bottom of an 11 x 12-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Melt 2 sticks butter; add sugar, egg and milk.
Bring to a boil, then cook 1 minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Spread over crackers in pan. Add a top layer of whole graham crackers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the carrots just until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add carrots and stir until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3/4 hour.
Serve cold as a salad or warm it and use as a side dish.
Refrigerate in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Yields 8 cups.
Good dish for potlucks!

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add molasses, peanut butter and egg.
Blend well.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Turn into a shallow glass casserole, 8 1/2 x 13-inch.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mary's fruit salad
directions: Soak the gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Combine the pineapple, cheese, lemon juice and sugar.
Cook (stirring constantly) until cheese dissolves. Add gelatin to the hot mixture and let boil up one time.
This usually takes about 5 minutes. Set aside and let cool.

title: harvest hamburger casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine beef, onion, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Layer the potatoes, flour, corn, lima beans and green pepper on top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from stove and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter. Beat.
Drop on wax paper, a spoon at a time.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
In another bowl, beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until light.
Stir in molasses and water.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour mixture and nuts to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: graham cracker pralines(microwave)
directions: Place a single layer of crackers in two 2-quart casserole dishes.
Soften butter in 1-quart measuring cup for 1 minute on 80%.
Stir in brown sugar and return to microwave for 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir in pecans and spread mixture over crackers. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Turn 1/4 turn midway through. Allow to cool slightly and cut into squares.
Remove from dish while slightly warm to wax paper to cool completely.
If using microwave baking sheet, cook 5 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Roll out and fry.

title: camp sausage
directions: Cut sausage into slices.
Cut up potatoes and boil until almost done.
Slice onion and bell pepper.
Place equal amounts of sausage, potato, onion and bell pepper in individual packages of foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Just before serving, grate cheese over sausage.
Can be served in foil.

title: spinach and brown rice casserole
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and saute onion, mushrooms and garlic until tender.
In a small bowl, mix egg, flour and cottage cheese. Add to sauteed vegetables along with the spinach. Stir in rice, pepper, thyme and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Turn into a greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish and top with remaining Parmesan cheese and sunflower seeds. Bake at 375° for at least 30 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together corn oil and sugar.
Beat in egg white.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves, gradually adding to first mixture.
Beat in applesauce and fold in nuts.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with Pam (or grease and flour pan) and pour in batter.
Makes 1 loaf.
Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes on cake rack.
(Can also be cooked inside of a 1 pound coffee can.)

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
With rotary mixer, beat butter and sugar until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each with a spoon.
Stir in vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Alternately stir in dry ingredients and milk.
Add nuts.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then cool on rack.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, parsley flakes and salt to taste. Drain, then add tomato sauce, spaghetti in cheese and tomato sauce and beans.
Mix. Cook over low heat; stir occasionally until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: key lime pie(the best)
directions: Mix in a saucepan the 1/2 cup sugar, gelatin, lime juice, salt and 1/2 cup water.
Heat until gelatin melts.
Beat egg yolks. Add hot mixture a little at a time so that the mixture doesn't curdle.
Cook over low heat and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the rind.
Chill until cool but not set.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Put half of crumbled crackers in bottom of casserole dish. Pour half of melted butter over crackers. Add cut up chicken (bite size). Mix soups, sour cream, pimentos, peas and chestnuts. Pour over chicken. Top with remaining crackers and butter. Cook at about 325° to 350° for 25 minutes until golden brown and bubbly. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, vegetable shortening, salt and 2 tablespoons water together, then if it is dry put more water.
Mix well, then roll out for pie crust.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla to creamed mixture; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Shape dough, by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar, place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a chocolate kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so cookie cracks around the edge.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: lynchburg lemonade
directions: Mix four parts white soda to 1 part remaining ingredients. Great summertime drink!

title: okra soup
directions: Combine ham hock, water, tomatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 1 hour.
Add 1 cup water, beans, okra, corn, salt and pepper to taste.
Reduce heat and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Stir milk and gravy mix in a small saucepan.
Stir over medium-high heat until boiling.
Reduce heat, stirring constantly. Simmer until thickened.
Put remaining ingredients except biscuits in pie plate.
Add gravy and mix.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°.
Place a border of biscuits on filling.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until biscuits are golden and filling is bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed flounder(student favorite)
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Combine vegetables and all other ingredients in mixing bowl.
Loosely stuff flounder with mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap tail in aluminum foil. Baste flounder with cooking oil or margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°, basting once.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in oil and oleo.
After melted, boil 1 minute.
Pour over popped corn, M&M's and nuts.
Mix well.
Press into angel food, Bundt or 9 x 13-inch well buttered pan.
Cool 2 hours before cutting.

title: blt spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, mustard and celery salt together.
Stir in bacon that has been crisply fried and crumbled, then diced tomatoes and chopped green pepper.
Cover and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: rolled cookies
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients.
Blend well with mixer on low speed 1 minute, then on medium speed 3 minutes.
Form ball; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll dough 1/8-inch on floured board.
Cut in desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Decorate as desired.
Can be tinted for holidays.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits and water together until done.
Add other ingredients and pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes; 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato and feta cheese
directions: Cut tomatoes into wedges.
In large bowl, combine tomatoes with next 6 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or longer, stirring occasionally.
To serve, drain tomatoes and sprinkle with Feta cheese.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat tortilla in hot oil to which chili powder has been added. Drain any liquid from chili.
Spread chili on tortillas. Sprinkle on onion and cheese and roll tortilla.
Put in baking dish and pour remainder of chili, cheese and onion on top.
Heat in 300° oven about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-timey coconut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Beat well but not too long.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk to the butter-sugar mixture, being sure to end with flour.
Grease 3 cake pans.
Put waxed paper in bottoms.
Pour in batter; bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool. Prepare filling.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops to taste.
Top with sliced onions. Sprinkle sugar and Worcestershire on meat; top with ketchup. Cover and bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a 6 to 8-inch plastic flowerpot and an artificial flower.

title: the melt
directions: Toast bread.
Make sandwich with ham and cheese.
Put in microwave for 45 seconds.
Now you have a yummy sandwich.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Put onion in butter and cook.
Add broccoli and cheese and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Add all other mixture.
Put mixture in casserole dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes in microwave.

title: nut brittle
directions: Heat the sugar gradually in clean smooth skillet.
Stir constantly in a bowl with a spoon until golden syrup is formed. Remove from the fire and stir in quickly the salt, soda and vanilla.
Pour the syrup over a layer of nuts in a greased pan. When cold, crack into small pieces.

title: vegetable meat casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly with onion.
Arrange all ingredients in dish and bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until thick. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup.
Place broccoli in a casserole dish and pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Dot with butter.
Crumble saltines over top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan french toast
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise and chives.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on 1 side of slices.
Place on broiler pan and broil about 1 minute or until toasty.
Turn slices over and use remainder of spread on untoasted side.
Broil second side.

title: butter dips
directions: Melt margarine in oven in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove pan as soon as margarine is melted.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk.
Stir slowly with fork until dough just clings together.
Turn on well floured board.
Roll over to coat with flour.
Knead lightly about 10 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick into a rectangle.
With a floured knife, cut dough in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 16 strips.
Dip each strip in butter on both sides and lay close together in 2 rows in pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup lemon juice and 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind. Blend condensed milk and egg yolks.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: frosted fruit
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Chill for several hours in freezer.
Put in refrigerator 1 hour before serving. (Can be made several days ahead but keep in freezer!)

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Brown beef. Add remaining ingredients and simmer till veggies are done. Freeze well. Make 5 qts.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Lightly grease the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Combine all ingredients in a bowl (reserve a little of each cheese to sprinkle on top).
Place mixture in the casserole dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until brown.
(You can add or subtract from the ingredients to suit your own taste.)
Serves 8.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix
together
corn,
egg
yolks, flour and seasonings. Fold whites
into
corn	mixture.
Melt butter in frying pan. Drop batter by spoonfuls on hot griddle and fry, turning only once. Serve with yogurt or applesauce.
Serves 4.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and lightly dust with flour two 9-inch square pans or three 8-inch round pans.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and beat.
Fold in carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan, about 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pans.
Frost with frosting following.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix
ingredients
and pour into greased casserole dish. Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with cracker crumbs (enough to top casserole)	and sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and brown on top (about 30 minutes).

title: orange jello mold
directions: Combine Jell-O, boiling water and orange juice.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks, along with juice from the pineapple. Pour into mold and set.
Before serving, mix instant pudding with milk.
Whip cream until stands in peaks.
Fold cream into the pudding.
Frost the Jell-O with this and serve.

title: mexican stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash and dry potatoes.
Wrap potatoes in foil and bake for 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
Remove potatoes from foil and cut in half.
Remove potato from skin and mash.
Save skins.
Combine garlic, salt, butter, green chiles, cilantro and cheese into potatoes and mix well.
Return mixture to potato skins.
Sprinkle more cheese on top and bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange cranberry torte
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; stir in nuts, dates, cranberries and orange rind.
In another bowl combine eggs, buttermilk and salad oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Let stand until lukewarm; remove to rack over large platter.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chicken.
Pour combined soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice over layers.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbling (35 minutes).

title: sherry custard
directions: Mix milk, lemon rind, salt and cinnamon stick in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Beat together eggs, sugar and cornstarch.
Add sherry.
Combine mixtures and bring slowly to a simmer.
Cook over very low heat until slightly thickened.
Either strain completely to remove lemon rind and cinnamon stick or simply remove cinnamon and leave lemon rind.
Pour into serving dishes.
Sprinkle powdered cinnamon on top and chill.
When serving, spoon a teaspoon of sherry on each serving (optional).

title: manor house poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer for two minutes.
Pour into two loaf pans, sprayed with Pam, then floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour or until tester comes out clean.
Cool slightly and remove from pans.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add water, chili mix and mix together. Add beans and tomato sauce. Heat for 10-15 minutes and serve for a nice hot bowl of chili.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Place chopped bacon on top and place in oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until bacon is brown.

title: refrigerator cheesecake
directions: Mix in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then press to form layer in bottom of pan.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt and soda and mix with first mixture.
Stir in milk well.
Dip hands in flour and form dough into small balls and place on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Flatten with a flat bottom glass dipped into sugar as each cookie is pressed.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Drain.
Add other ingredients (salt, pepper, onion, celery, green pepper, tomato sauce, catsup, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce).
Cook 30 minutes.

title: easy corn dogs
directions: Combine cornmeal mix and pepper.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Insert wooden skewer in one end of each hot dog.
Coat with additional flour; dip into cornmeal batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil, buttermilk and sugar. Sift dry ingredients and mix one cup at a time.
Bake on an ungreased pan at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool.
Pull from bones in medium-size pieces. In large pot, combine sauce, onion, pepper and seasonings.
Add about 1/2 cup chicken broth for flavor.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
While simmering, boil spaghetti and drain.
Add chicken to sauce at this time and simmer for last 10 minutes.
Combine sauce and spaghetti and stir thoroughly.
Good meal with salad and garlic toast.

title: vinegar chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil on stove.
Remove from heat.
Place raw chicken pieces in hot mixture.
Marinate for 2 hours.
Broil or grill (about 20 minutes) until done.

title: italian beef
directions: Put
1 cup water in a pan with roast.
Bake until almost done. Save
broth.
Cool.
Slice
thin
and add slices back to broth. Add
2 bouillon cubes (more if using leftover roast and have
no broth).
Add
spices
and
green
peppers.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves and serve on hard rolls.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken and rice)
directions: Boil chicken until tender (about 45 minutes).
Fry rice until golden brown.
Then add diced onion and tomato sauce.
Fill pan halfway with chicken broth (approximately 3 cups).
Then add boiled chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: greek loaf
directions: In bread machine pan, place first seven ingredients in order suggested by manufacturer.
Select Basic Bread Setting.
Check dough after 5 minutes of mixing.
Add 1 to 2 Tbsp. water or flour, if needed.
Just before the final kneading, add olives.

title: peach cobbler 2
directions: Heat 1/2 cup sugar and fruit (or sweeten to taste).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in Pyrex dish in oven. Mix the flour, 2/3 cup sugar and milk in mixing bowl. Beat like batter. Take dish from oven.
Pour batter in it over the melted margarine.
Pour heated fruit over batter. Stir slightly to blend. Bake 25 minutes or until brown. Do not cover.
Fruits other than peaches may be used.

title: rowdy's homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook meat, onions, mushrooms and peppers (in fry pan) until hamburger is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add all other ingredients and cook for 1 to 2 hours.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in the order given and let stand in the refrigerator 7 to 8 hours or overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and flour. In heavy saucepan on low heat, melt butter or margarine. Add sugar mixture, then egg yolks along with milk. Cook until thick. Doesn't take long. Add vanilla flavoring. Put in baked shell. Top with meringue. Cook until brown. Makes 1 large pie.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Heat 2 cups of cottage cheese until lukewarm and add sugar, minced onion, margarine, dill seed, salt, soda and eggs.
Add softened yeast and flour.
Mix well.
Cover with cup towel and let rise for about 1 hour in a warm place.
Stir down.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan, cover and let rise again until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
After baking, butter the top and sprinkle with salt.

title: casserole onions
directions: Peel
onions and boil whole in salted water.
When cool, remove centers from onions, chop and combine with other materials. Stuff
onion
shells
with
mixture.
Make white sauce of flour, butter,
milk
and salt and pour over onions which have been placed in a buttered baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: mamma's italian dressing
directions: In bowl combine salt and seasonings.
Add oil and mix.
Add vinegar slowly, continue to mix.
Taste to adjust for personal preference.

title: double chocolate shortcakes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine until dough forms.
Turn onto cloth-covered surface well dusted with baking mix; gently smooth dough into a ball.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 3-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until done, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spicy hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients with ground beef.
Pat the meat according to your wishes.
Grill it.
Hamburger is ready for serving.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: biscuit surprise
directions: Dip marshmallows completely in melted margarine, then roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Wrap each marshmallow in a biscuit, sealing dough completely.
Bake in muffin tin at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Messy, but worth it!

title: aunt garlene's peach pizza
directions: Layer 1:
Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and melted butter. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool well before proceeding with next layer.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Prick the surface of the pastry shell with a fork.
Prebake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: goldenrod eggs
directions: Chop eggs and add to white sauce with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over toast.
Grate or press yolks through sieve; sprinkle over eggs.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Steam chicken with onion and celery leaves until tender (about 1 hour), then bone chicken.
Cook broccoli.
In buttered pan (9 x 13-inch), layer broccoli.
Mix together soup, Miracle Whip, curry powder and lemon juice. Spread over chicken.
Spread grated cheese (save some) over soup mixture, then crumble Ritz crackers over grated cheese and then rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes. Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown venison in skillet. Saute garlic cloves and onion; add to venison. Add tomato sauce, beans and spices. Cook together for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and milk in which soda has been added.
Add bananas, salt, nuts and flour. Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook the 2 cups rice the night before.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine, soup, broth and sour cream together over low heat.
Place chicken on top of crackers in casserole dish and pour over mixture.
Cut French bread and place on top; brown.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for one hour, covered with plastic wrap.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add flour, salt,
cinnamon and soda to sugar mixture.
Blend in egg/raisin mixture, oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Dough will be stiff. Drop by heaping teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Delicious secret is soaking of raisins.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: oglethorpe corn bread
directions: Stove Top Instructions:
Premelt fat drippings in skillet, just enough to cover bottom good.
A seasoned cast-iron skillet works best.

title: easy munchy mix
directions: Mix and eat!.
(Seasonally festive with "holiday" M&M's.)

title: lean gravy
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in approximately 1/4 cup stock. Whisk in remaining stock while cooking over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Contains 23 calories, 0.3 grams fat (12% of fat from calories).

title: broccoli salad iii
directions: Combine and mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; let set aside for 10 minutes.
Chop broccoli into bite size pieces and mix together with raisins, red onion, bacon and cheese, then add mayonnaise mixture.
Refrigerate.
Best if made the night before.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and cover each breast with a cheese slice.
Mix soup, wine and stuffing mix and pour over chicken.
Drizzle with the melted margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Add hominy, tomatoes, crumbled sausage and seasonings.
Cook for 20 minutes.
In a casserole layer hominy mixture and cheese alternately until all is used.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite snack:  peanut butter coffee
directions: You toast the bread.
Then you put peanut butter on the bread. Then make the coffee. Then, dip the peanut butter bread in the coffee and taste.
Enjoy!

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour and cocoa.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread with a jar of marshmallow cream, then spread with frosting.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar in a lightly greased shallow 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
In another bowl, combine brown sugar and flour.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; stir in oats and pecans.
Sprinkle mixture over cranberries and apples.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: chop and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in a baking dish.
Stir in melted butter.
Place chops on top of rice.
Pour can of soup over chops.
Add 1/2 to 1 package dry onion soup mix over mixture according to your taste. Add 1 cup water and cook, covered with foil, for 1 hour at 350° to 375°.
Check for dryness and add water, if needed.
Remove foil to brown, if desired.

title: beet jelly
directions: Clean beets thoroughly and cook in 6 cups water, boiling slowly so you will have 4 cups liquid.
Measure juice and add pectin.
Bring to a boil; add sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes, then add Kool-Aid.
Stir well.
Let cool slightly; pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on medium heat for approximately 3 to 4 hours or until meat is tender.

title: autumn medley stew
directions: In a large soup pan, simmer onion and chicken breasts in 2 cups water.
When chicken breasts are cooked, debone and set aside.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, pepper and spices to onion and broth mixture.
Add deboned chicken to stew.
Simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are done.
Add rice and simmer 10 extra minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: cold mexican corn salad
directions: Mix corn and sour cream.
Chill before serving.
Add chips and mix well.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
In separate bowl combine cake flour and baking powder. Add to cream mixture.
Add milk and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tuna roll-ups appetizer
directions: Make tuna salad as usual; set aside.
Lay out each crescent roll and cut in half lengthwise.
Stuff each half with a tablespoon of tuna mix and roll up, squeezing edges together. Bake, following time for crescent rolls.
Serve hot.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix as any layer cake.
Preheat oven to 500° to 550°.
Use an iron griddle.
Spray with Pam.
Put 3 1/2 large tablespoons of batter to the first two layers, then start using three spoons for other layers.
Bake each layer for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
When lightly brown, they are ready to stack on cake plate and start icing.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, salad oil, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Pour mixture over cabbage and mix thoroughly.
Best, if left to marinate for at least an hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Crush potato chips and place a thin layer in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add a layer of tuna.
Pour mixture of milk and soup over this.
Then bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: vegetable bars
directions: *Use broccoli, grated carrots, green pepper, mushrooms, onions, cauliflower, grated cheese, diced tomatoes, black olives.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and form loaf.
Place in 2-inch pan and spread catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine in heavy saucepan caramels and evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted.
Keep warm.
Combine in large bowl all remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
Stir with fork until crumbly but hold together. Press 1/2 dough in cake pan.
Save rest for topping.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over all.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top. Press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zesty italian tuna spread
directions: Drain oil or water from tuna, rinse in cold water.
Cut the olives in fourths.
Mix olives, salad dressing mix and sour cream together; combine this with the tuna.
Mix well.
Put in dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve on crackers or in a sandwich.

title: a multitude of sins
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in 2 cups boiling water. Chill until it thickens.
Add cheese, celery, pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Combine whipped cream and mayonnaise and fold into first mixture.
Chill for 12 hours before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices. Place in greased pizza pan or small cookie sheet.
Make sure pieces are overlapping.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and set aside.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, salsa and chili powder.
Stir in chicken breasts to coat.
Boil 5 minutes on first side and 4 to 5 minutes on second side.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mount into ball.
Pour sauce on top and add shrimp.
Dip with cracker or chips.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Mix water, onions, horseradish, salad dressing, salt and pepper and pour over the cooked carrots.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs and butter or margarine.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Mix water and other ingredients and bring to boil; add frozen fish.
Bring to boil; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt 1 stick of butter.
Serve haddock with butter.
Makes 2 servings.

title: crab balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in cracker
crumbs and fry.

title: red cinnamon pickles
directions: Day 1:
Peel, core and slice cucumbers to make rings.
Mix 1 cup lime with enough water to cover cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Add to vermicelli the Accent, seasoned salt, lemon juice and oil.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate top oatmeal bars
directions: Cream spry and sugars thoroughly.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add flour and oats; mix well.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate with margarine.
Spread on top.
Add nuts.

title: french toast
directions: Dip both sides of bread into egg and milk mixture.
Fry in a dab of oil.
Serve with butter and powdered sugar.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Slice avocados in a small bowl with lemon juice to prevent discoloring.
Wash and trim cauliflower, broccoli and tomatoes. Mix all vegetables.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot pickle peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Place in Mason jars.
Heat vinegar to a boil and pour over peppers.
Be sure vinegar covers peppers.
Seal jars.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind, chop and mix the cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil.
Add vegetables to boiling mixture; boil for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Seal and process in water bath.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions with salt and pepper; mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in a large casserole and bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Similar to cabbage rolls without the time consumed!

title: jane's chocolate mousse
directions: Pour all of the ingredients into a blender and whip for about 30 seconds to 1 minute, until smooth.
Pour immediately into individual serving glasses or dishes and refrigerate until serving time.

title: swift creek mill bread
directions: Pour simmering water over sugar, margarine and salt.
Stir; cool slightly and add yeast, eggs and flour in that order.
Let rise in a bowl until doubled in size.
Beat down and spoon bread dough into greased pans (two loaf pans or 1 tube pan).
Let rise until 1 inch from top of pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour for tube pan or 35 minutes for loaf pans.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Boil water and add to jello.
Mix and let cool.
Roll out grahams.
Add melted butter and powdered sugar.
Pat down for crust in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with fork and add sugar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add Bisquick, banana and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and honey. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt until blended.
Stir in oats.
Fill 16 to 20 muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Delicious warm or cold.

title: hearty hodgepodge in crock-pot
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Add all remaining ingredients except cream cheese.
Stir well.
Slice cream cheese and place on top. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order given:
eggs, vanilla, baking powder, zucchini, baking soda, nuts, oil, salt, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes in 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Easy to make, easy to freeze.
Tastes great!

title: chocolate candy
directions: Put margarine, bitter chocolate (cut in small pieces) and semi-sweet chocolate in large pan.
Put milk and sugar in heavy saucepan and turn on low until sugar dissolves, then turn higher until it starts to boil.
Cook for 7 minutes while boiling, stirring all the time.
Pour this over margarine and chocolates and beat until all melts and begins to get stiff.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in buttered pans and refrigerate until cold.
Cut in squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in crust.
Freeze until hard.
Serve frozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white sugar and cinnamon in medium container, preferably with a lid.
Drop pieces of biscuits, a few at a time, in container. Shake to coat.
Place in tube baking pan.
Melt margarine. Add brown sugar and syrup. Stir together.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Chopped nuts or raisins may be added.

title: microwave potato ring mold
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, butter and eggs.
Season with paprika and salt to taste.
Pour into a micro ring mold; then pour 1/3 cup of milk on top and cover.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Turn half way through cooking time.
"You are the salt of the earth." Matthew 5:13.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli; drain off water.
Add cream of celery soup and cheese to broccoli.
Stir well; pour in baking dish.
Melt stick of butter; add crumbled Ritz crackers in butter.
Put on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chewy butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add sugar and bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Drop in eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla and sifted flour and baking powder.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour in buttered pan and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: quaker fruit 'n oat bars
directions: Grease 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Combine all ingredients except preserves.
Mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup oat mixture.
Press remaining onto bottom of prepared dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer cheese balls
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze.
Makes 2.
Keep frozen. Thaw before serving.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together by hand and spoon into cold muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. This will make 6 rolls.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix fruits and flour together.
Mix in large pan the following:
eggs, butter, sugar, jelly, figs and 4 cups flour. Add fruits to mixture and pour into greased and floured pans.
You can put mixture in 3 tube pans and cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool and remove from pans.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick.
Thin with canned milk and add heaping tablespoon salad dressing.
You don't need very much milk.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of pan. Set aside.
Do not use mixer!
Hand mix all ingredients in bowl. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Frost this cake while it's hot!!!!!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and egg yolks. Heat water and butter until melted. Add this to first mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick.
Pour into baked deep dish pie shell. Top with meringue and brown.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown the beef and onion in skillet.
Add beans and bake about 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole; spread 1 can of asparagus, half of sliced eggs, half of white sauce. Repeat. Melt about 1 tablespoon butter; add bread crumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together, adding 7-Up last.
Make 3 layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and flour and mix well.
Add nuts.
Form dough into small balls about size of marble.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
While still hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1
hour.

title: microwave pork chop bake
directions: Combine sauerkraut, onion and brown sugar in 10 x 6-inch utility dish or 12 x 8-inch dish.
Toss lightly with fork. Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Arrange over sauerkraut with meaty portions toward outside of dish.
Top with soup.

title: pepper pickles
directions: Bring to boil vinegar, water, salt and alum.
After boiling, keep hot when pouring.
Have garlic, dill and pepper with cucumbers packed tightly in jars.
Pour hot mixture over top. Seal and put in water bath 10 to 15 minutes, then let cool.

title: pollo guisada(chicken stew)
directions: Cut chicken and wash it well.
Add lime juice, salt, onion, pepper, garlic and coriander and let it sit for about 1 hour.
In a big saucepan, put oil and sugar; heat.
Wait until the sugar burns.
Add chicken and move occasionally until it is brown all over.
Add wine, water and tomato soup.
Cook over low heat until the chicken is tender.
Serve over rice or with potatoes.

title: hot chocolate for a crowd
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add hot water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk; heat to serving temperature, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Cook 3 minutes and put in sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Bake according to directions on the cake box in a 13 x 9 greased pan at 350°. Frost with favorite frosting. Chocolate is great!

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Let eggs, cream and butter stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
In skillet, cook bacon until brown.
Beat together eggs and cream until blended.
Toss salad pasta with butter.
Pour egg mixture over and toss until coated.
Add bacon, cheese, tomato, green pepper and parsley.
Season to taste.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions according to directions on box.
Cook rice separately.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barb's meat loaf
directions: Mix together. Shape into loaf.
Put 1/2 cup water in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french onion soup(vegetarian)
directions: Heat oil or water in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions and cook for 2 minutes.
Add flour and stir until the onions are well coated.
Add water and soy sauce.
Stir well. Bring soup to a boil; then simmer over low heat until the onions are tender.
Add more water if soup becomes too thick.

title: italian cube steak
directions: Season cube steak with garlic salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet.
Mix eggs in bowl and dip steak on both sides in eggs. Pour 1/2 cup bread crumbs in a large bowl; put steak in crumbs. Bread well on both sides.
Place breaded steaks into skillet and cook for 10 minutes, turning once.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hand.
Shape loosely into balls (bite size).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add next 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Make balls the size of walnuts.
Press flat.
Can also be made in a roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator and slice later.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: eleanora's never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat the egg in 1 cup measuring cup.
Add vinegar; fill with water to make 1 full cup.
Add the egg, vinegar and water mixture to the flour mixture. This can be rolled and rerolled and still have a good texture. Great for beginners.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together.
Slowly add eggs one at a time.
Then add oil and 7-Up.
Mix well.
Pour half of this mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix together the sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Pour half of this into the pan. Repeat these steps again.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: traveling tacos(jamie mitchell's favorite recipe)
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread mixture on bottom of serving dish, then layer lettuce, pepper, onion and tomato.
Top with taco sauce and shredded cheese.

title: toad in a hole
directions: Cut 3-inch hole (or hole big enough to hold an egg) in middle of bread slice.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
When margarine bubbles, add bread.
Immediately crack egg into hole and cook until bread begins to turn brown, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn over with spatula and brown other side.
Serve hot.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: *May substitute diced cucumbers for relish.

title: christmas gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add pineapple juice; cool. Combine remaining ingredients and add to gelatin mixture. Pour into an oblong pan; Chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.

title: cream pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: bubble cake
directions: Thaw dough.
Melt butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Pinch off pieces the size of walnuts from one loaf.
Roll in butter, then in the sugar mixture.
Place in greased 10-inch tube pan.
One loaf makes 2 rows around the pan.
Sprinkle this layer with nuts, raisins or coconut, if desired.
Do the same with second loaf. Pour any remaining butter and sugar on top.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
(Place a cookie sheet under 2 piece tube pan.)
Remove from pan immediately.

title: baked barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon, in a heavy pot. Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Place over top of beans.
Cover and set on back of grill.
Cook over a slow fire, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If you prefer, you may bake beans in an oven and keep hot on back of grill.

title: cashew-shrimp salad
directions: Prepare dressing by mixing the first 4 ingredients. Refrigerate.
Combine the next 5 ingredients.
Add dressing; mix thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper; toss gently again. Place lettuce leaf on plate.
Spoon salad into center of leaves. Toss a few cashews on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Peas can be added for color.

title: brenda's rice and chicken
directions: Mix soup and milk; set aside.
Brown chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Thaw broccoli.
Combine all ingredients in a skillet, mix thoroughly and heat through.

title: fran's sleepover goulash
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, tomato paste, water and onion.
Mix well.
Simmer slowly 15 to 20 minutes or until flavors blend.
Add seasoning to taste.
Serve over hamburger rolls.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Form into balls; put in skillet and brown.
Pour off grease.
Cover with soup (for double batch use 3 cans).
Simmer for 25 minutes or until done.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: chocolate delight bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a large bowl, pour milk and gradually add the pudding mixes. Beat with a whisk until well blended, approximately one minute. Stir in the bread cubes and nuts. Pour mixture into a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle the chocolate chips evenly over the top. Bake 40 minutes or until pudding is bubbly. Remove from oven.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs, mix until smooth. Combine caramels and milk in a microwave safe bowl and cook at full power for approximately 1 minute, stirring often. Add pecans to melted caramels. Pour into pie crust. Top with cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Serve with chocolate and/or caramel sauce on top.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli as directed, omitting salt.
Drain and place in baking dish.
Gradually add milk, onion, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add rest of ingredients. Beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Chill 5 hours.

title: cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to sit on pan for 5 minutes and then remove.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in a bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat to blend.
Blend in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend in, but do not overmix.
Lastly, fold in the carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Turn batter into a buttered 10-inch tube or a Bundt pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto rack.
Frost as desired when cake is completely cooled.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Split tamales and lay in bottom of baking dish.
Save some of the cheese (or add a bit more) for top of mixture.
I alternate the Fritos too and put quite a few on top.
Bake for full hour, oven temperatures vary.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet at 375.
Drop batter by 1 tsp. into oil.
Fry 2-3 minutes until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Dust with confectioners sugar. Serve with syrup.

title: hard sauce(for gingerbread and steamed puddings)
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; add flour and water.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add nutmeg and vanilla.

title: lo-cal orange blossom dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine pudding mix with orange juice and blend thoroughly. Gently fold in the mandarin oranges.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sliced cucumbers and onions together.
Cover with water and add 1 tablespoon salt.
Let stand for 2 hours and drain good for 1 hour.
Boil sugar and vinegar.
Cool.
Pour over pickles. Add celery salt and mustard seed.
Stir and refrigerate.
(Add green pepper and garlic, if desired.)

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: magic muffins
directions: Mix and stir until flour is moistened. Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: party surprise loaf
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast,
sugar and salt in a large bowl. Add margarine and water and mix well with electric mixer.
Add egg substitute and 1 cup flour, beating 1 minute on high speed.
Stir in oatmeal and enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn onto lightly floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with towel and let rest 20 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Fix enough vanilla wafer crumbs to cover bottom of 9x12 dish. Beat egg whites till fluffy.
Add sugar, cool whip and strawberries. Mix well. Pour over crumbs and freeze, covered. Spread crumbs on top also.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all together in food processor.
You can use orange, lime or lemon juice and rind.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Combine all other ingredients with beef.
Pour into casserole dish; bake at 375°
for 10 minutes, then top with 1 can of biscuits and bake 20 minutes more.

title: chicken wings teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken in shallow pan and marinate at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Remove from marinade and brown 30 minutes, basting frequently with marinade. Turn once during cooking.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put salt in water and add sliced cucumbers and onions.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Pack cucumbers and onions in jars.
Add sugar, vinegar, turmeric, mustard and celery seed together and bring to a boil, then pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Heat soup and water and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (or until tender).
Uncover last 15 minutes of baking.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, crumbs and powdered sugar. Press in pan sprayed with Pam.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top.
Chill before cutting.
Makes 54 pieces using 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on the package.
Mix Eagle Brand condensed milk and Cool Whip with pudding.
Cut bananas and add to the pudding.
Layer bowl with cookies and pudding.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg with milk and add to dry ingredients.
Knead out lightly on floured board. Roll out thin and fill.
Fry in oil.

title: easy caramel sauce
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 220°. Remove from heat; stir in butter, whipping cream and vanilla. Serve warm over ice cream or pound cake.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt in saucepan the shortening.
Take off the stove and add brown sugar.
Set aside to cool.
When cooled, add the egg, then blend in the flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in vanilla. Spread in a greased square 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix dry pudding mix and powdered sugar.
Add milk.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place a layer of whole graham crackers in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add a layer of pudding mix. Repeat the layers of crackers and then pudding mix.
Last, add a layer of crackers and top with a can of chocolate frosting.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: glen campbell chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and milk.
Add sour cream and stir. Add chocolate cake mix and beat well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured tube (or Bundt) pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If desired, frost with thin chocolate glaze while hot.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries
(discard
any
that are soft or blemished). Wash
oranges,
do not peel.
Put cranberries, apples and oranges through
medium blade of a grinder or food processor.
Drain off excess juice; reserve.
Add sugar, stir.
Pour 1/2 to 3/4
of
the reserved
juice
into
the relish (relish should be very
moist, but not runny).
Chill 24 hours.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; drain on paper towel. Reserve 1-2 Tbsp. drippings. Add eggs, salt and pepper to drippings; cook and stir over medium heat until eggs are completely set. Spoon 1/4 cup of egg mixture down the center of each tortilla; sprinkle with cheese, onions and bacon. Fold bottom and sides of tortilla over filling.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with marshmallow cream in a bowl until smooth and creamy. (May chill overnight.) Serve with your favorite fresh fruit (apples, bananas, grapes, pineapple, oranges, etc.).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add liquids.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325°.
Add 3 tablespoons of sugar to each egg white for topping.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If you like, you can put grated cheese on top.

title: pear goody
directions: Bring sugar and water to simmer.
Peel, core and quarter pears and add to simmering water-sugar mixture.
Cook gently until pears are slightly translucent.
Add cranberries and raisins and continue to simmer until the cranberry skins split and the raisins are plump.
Makes 1 quart.
Very good with ham.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix; sprinkle top with one cup crushed flakes.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: maxine's spinach
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil with bacon slices.
Add spinach; simmer about 20 minutes.
Add butter, garlic powder and salt. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: caesar salad
directions: Whisk the first 8 ingredients in a small bowl.	Combine lettuce, as many croutons
as
desired,
cheese and a generous amount of pepper in a
large
bowl.
Add
dressing.
Toss well and serve.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Put browned meatballs into mixture and cook in crock-pot at least one hour.

title: hobo meatball stew
directions: In small bowl, combine ketchup, vinegar, salt, basil and pepper; set aside.
Cut heavy-duty aluminum foil in 4 pieces about 12 x 16-inches.
Place meatballs and vegetables, equally divided on foil pieces.
Pour ketchup mixture, equally divided over meatballs and vegetables.
Fold sides of foil over and seal tightly to make 4 packages.
Grill in hot barbecue coals or place on cookie sheet and bake in 425° oven about 40 minutes until done.

title: red beets - canned
directions: Wash red beets and cook in hot water so skins come off.
Peel off skins and cut into desired size.
Place into jars.
Mix ingredients together and boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over top of red beets and seal.
Cold pack 10 to 15 minutes.
Can adjust to your own taste.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add persimmon; beat again.
