Add milk, then flour sifted with dry ingredients.
Grease double boiler.
Steam 2 hours without lifting the lid.
Serve with cream.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 15 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Blend cream cheese, milk and pudding.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread well drained pineapple over cream layer.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle top with coconut or nuts.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: Cut sirloin steak into small pieces.
Cook in small amount of vegetable oil the steak and chicken pieces.
Drain off fat.
Add 1 package of frozen stir-fry vegetables.
Stir in some soy sauce. Cook until vegetables begin to get tender.
Add mushrooms and pineapple.
Cook until done, adding more soy sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken and dumplings the easy way
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a full boil.
Add bouillon cubes, chicken and salt; cook until chicken is well done.
Remove breasts from stock and set aside to cool.
Keep stock at a rolling boil and break biscuits into small pieces, one can at a time, until desired consistency.
Tear chicken into bite size pieces and add to dumplings.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on very low heat for 20 minutes.

title: diet eclairs
directions: In saucepan, heat water and oil to boiling.
Add flour and salt; beat together.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spoon pastry onto nonstick cookie sheet in 3-inch strips (approximately 1 x 3-inches).
Leave room for spreading.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool before filling 9 puffs, 68 calories each.

title: savory braised steaks
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil and brown steaks over medium-high heat.
Remove steaks, reserving drippings.
In drippings, cook onion, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in Italian herb with tomato soup mix blended with water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Return steaks to skillet and simmer covered 15 minutes. Stir in artichoke hearts, then sprinkle steaks with cheese, olives and parsley.
Continue simmering 5 minutes or until steaks are tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle extra crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Boil potatoes,	onion
and
celery until tender.
Drain and reserve
1	cup
liquid.
Coarsely mash vegetables.
Brown sausage and
add
to
potato mixture and reserved liquid.
Add soup.
If too
thick, add milk.
Makes an excellent supper for on the road. Serve with Italian bread and fresh fruit.

title: sherry or rum peppers
directions: Soak 10 to 12 Bermuda peppers or small hot red peppers in 8 to 10 ounces sherry or black rum (try to find Gosling Rum, which may be available from the ABC store on 70 just south of Raleigh). After 10 days of soaking the peppers, strain out the residue and retain the liquid in a shake bottle.
Use carefully until the pepper retention is noted.
This is the hot sauce of Bermuda.

title: the ultimate macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix the cooked macaroni with the remaining ingredients. Spread in a small casserole. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: bishop salad
directions: Just layer all the ingredients.
Cover for at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over first four ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all these ingredients.
Mix well and pour into prepared crust and bake according to directions.
Cool on a rack and transfer to serving dish.

title: baked hominy and cheese
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg.
Add hominy, cheese, milk, onion, bacon, butter and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, until bubbly and top begins to brown.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Place macaroni in a bowl and cover with boiling water.
Set aside while macaroni blanches.
Saute ground beef and onions together in a large saucepan until beef loses redness and onions are transparent.
Drain fat.
Drain macaroni and add to meat along with remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: relish
directions: Use coarse blade on grinder. Combine all vegetables in large bowl. Sprinkle with salt; cover with cold water. Let stand 4 hours. Drain in colander. Press excess liquid out.

Combine sugar, vinegar and seeds. Bring to boil. Stir until sugar dissolves. Stir in drained vegetables. Simmer 10 minutes. Pack into sterilized jars and seal. Hot water bath 10 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: cheese squash with bread crumb topping
directions: Cook squash in skillet on top of stove over medium heat, until tender; add onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in slowly flour and water paste, until there is a thick consistency.
Turn off heat.
Pour into casserole dish; add cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Place in oven on broil on center rack until crumbs are golden brown.
Remove from oven; serve.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Mix cooked chicken, sour cream and soup together.
Pour in greased dish.
Mix crackers and melted oleo. Spread over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is baking cook last 4 ingredients together. When cake is done, spread over top while both are hot.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread mix, using water instead of milk.
After it has cooled, crumble it and mix with all remaining ingredients.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in roaster pan.
Add enough water to just cover roast.
Add salt, pepper, and onions (quartered).
Bake in a roaster pan approximately 2 hours or until roast begins to get tender.
Cut carrots, potatoes, and celery into quarters.
Place on roast.
When vegetables are almost tender, combine 2 packages Au Jus gravy mix with 3/4 cups water.
Stir well.
Pour over roast and vegetables.
Simmer another 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: german pork chops
directions: Brown chops in butter in Dutch oven or thick pot.
Add onions and cook lightly.
Add apples and drained sauerkraut; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover with wine and cover.
Cook in oven 1 hour at 375°.
You can also put some potatoes in if desired.

title: christmas peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in a heavy pan.
Heat and stir until mixture boils.
Cook rapidly to 236° on a candy thermometer. Slowly stir in peanuts.
Keep mixture bubbling.
Cook to 280° on thermometer, stir constantly.
Stir in butter, cook to 300°. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Sprinkle soda over the top. Stir for 15 seconds until it is puffy.
Pour into a buttered pan. Cool, break into pieces.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Combine; stir. Let stand 3 weeks. Stir 2 times a week.

title: banana waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl combine yogurt, coconut and cinnamon; mix well. Add celery, raisins and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Gently stir bananas into yogurt mixture.
Chill several hours.

title: layered salad
directions: Pour on the layered ingredients and store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Toss lightly before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese; add sugar, milk and peanut butter. Add Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust. Let set at least an hour in refrigerator. Can be frozen.

title: julian's carrots(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Into small saucepan, add juice from pineapple and orange juice.
In a small bowl, mix cornstarch, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in a few tablespoons of juice mixture and mix to a smooth paste.
Heat juice, then stir in cornstarch.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks and cut carrots.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until hot and bubbly.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Precook the macaroni.
In saucepan, heat the soup, tuna, milk and bell pepper.
Add the macaroni and let simmer for 5 minutes. Let sit without heat until macaroni swells.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil or simmer beef and pork in a large kettle with onions for about 2 hours (until meat is falling off bones).
Boil chicken the last hour or in a separate pot.
Remove meat and chill broth. Remove fat.

Add tomatoes, okra and butter beans to broth to be cooking while working with meat. Take skin, bones and excess fat from meats, then chop meats very fine. When vegetables are done, add meats and corn and cook on low about 20 minutes, stirring more or less constantly to keep corn from sticking while it thickens the stew. This freezes well.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Pour boiling water over the four vegetables.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Rinse under cold water and set aside.
In 2 tablespoons oil, saute tomatoes, 1 teaspoon garlic, parsley, salt and pepper for 3 minutes.
Set aside and keep warm.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Dredge chops in flour; reserve excess flour.
In a large Dutch oven melt butter and brown chops on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
Stir reserved flour into pan and stir.
Whisk in 1 1/2 cups apple juice.
Return chops to pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and remaining apple juice.
Cover and bake until done, about 30 more minutes.

title: italian delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef in oil.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and place in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: my mother's one-two-three-four cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one is added.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and add alternately with milk and vanilla to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pans lined with waxed paper and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.
Or bake in a tube-cake pan in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Make biscuit dough.
Roll thin and spread with uncooked sausage.
Roll into small jelly rolls.
Chill, slice and bake.

title: charlotte's special ham casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Heat in medium oven until cheese melts.

title: ozark apple pie
directions: Mix in order given in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Grease 1 (10-inch) pie pan.
Pour mixture in pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.
Good dessert when apples are plentiful.
Best served warm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: smothered hamburger steaks and onions
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions and gravy.
Shape into 4 large patties.
Brown on one side in greased skillet.
Turn, add onion and brown lightly.
Add gravy. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ranch bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine honey, buttermilk, salt, Molly McButter, Ranch dressing mix and fat-free mayonnaise. Stir and warm mixture slightly.
Do not boil; set aside.

In a large bowl, combine 3 1/2 cups of flour with yeast and mix. Gradually add warm buttermilk mixture to flour and mix thoroughly. Gradually add almost all remaining flour (reserve 1/2 cup) and continue to mix.
Turn dough out on floured surface and use remaining 1/2 cup flour while kneading dough when it becomes too sticky.
Knead dough for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place dough in large bowl sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Spray top of the dough lightly, also.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Add egg, shortening, sugar and milk.
Beat only until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill well oiled muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: tuna vegetable casserole
directions: Cook onions in margarine. Stir in flour and bouillon. Add thyme and pepper. Add milk; stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in tuna, Veg-All and parsley. Cook until heated.
Immediately pour into casserole dish. Quarter biscuits; place on top of casserole. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Mix everything in a bowl.
Spoon this mixture into buns.
Wrap buns in foil.
Place wrapped buns on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 burgers.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy skillet or cake pan.	Add brown sugar and heat until blended.
Arrange pineapple and maraschino cherries, if desired.
Blend egg yolk, pineapple juice and sugar. Add flour, baking powder and salt.	Beat egg whites to form stiff peaks and fold into batter.
Pour over pineapple and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Place plate over cake pan and invert to remove the cake from the pan while hot.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over popcorn already popped.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 200°.

title: noodle candy
directions: In double boiler, melt chips, then add noodles; mix.
Put spoonfuls onto wax paper; cool.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Rub a 2-quart baking dish with margarine.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into casserole dish.
Top with buttery crackers, crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 10.

title: taco meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Form into small meatballs and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, add remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Place in covered container and marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator. Drain 30 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy enchilada sauce
directions: Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Pour over enchiladas. Use leftovers for dip.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Tear dried beef into small pieces.
Over medium heat in saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine.
Stir in dried beef pieces.
Gradually stir in flour until blended.
Slowly add milk. Stir constantly to avoid lumping.
Remove from heat.
Season with pepper to taste.
Pour over toast or biscuits.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Boil ribs until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Bake ribs in sauce (uncovered) at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn once while baking.

title: new england pumpkin pie
directions: Whisk all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for awhile.

title: hoosier hill pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and then butter.
Add walnuts and chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips.
Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor and blend.

title: fruit punch slush
directions: Boil water and sugar 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine in blender lemons, pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Leave chunky. Add to boiled sugar mixture.
Add bottled ginger ale and pineapple juice, freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 to 4 hours before ready to serve.
Keep pouring the remaining 2 bottles of ginger ale all over the punch while serving.

title: cheese roll-ups
directions: Cut crust from bread (white or brown).
Spread with a thick mixture of your favorite grated cheese and butter or margarine. Roll up the bread.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Bake in 350° oven until browned.
Delicious with soup or beverage.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Then mix all ingredients together, leaving cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake with lid on dish at 400° for 30 to 34 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onions, peppers and tomatoes in margarine for 30 minutes to 1 hour, then add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic. Keep simmering and add soup and shrimp (no water is added to this, but can be thinned with tomato juice).
Simmer all together about 2 hours.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: cheese peas
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and gradually stir in flour.
Slowly stir in milk until thickened.
Add grated cheese.
Drain peas and add to cheese sauce.
Continue to simmer over low heat for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in order given; chill 4 hours.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, soda and corn syrup in very large saucepan and bring to soft boil (234° to 238° on candy thermometer).
Just before removing from heat, add pecans.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss and holds its shape.
Drop on wax paper in mounds.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling (approximately 5 minutes) until thick. Add butter, lemon rind and lemon juice. This is good over bread pudding or gingerbread.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine corn flakes with butter; top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Place spices in cheesecloth.
Boil water, sugar and spices until sugar dissolves.
Add juices and extract.
Heat and serve.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Mix first six ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave until hot, 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add rest of the ingredients and microwave until hot and cheese is melted, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour and flavoring.
Fold in the 7-Up; mix well. Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: zucchini bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Refrigerate 1 quart of the cider and pour remaining 1 quart into a saucepan with the spices.
Cook 15 minutes and strain to remove spices.

title: pepper chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with garlic salt and onion, chopped. Save broth.
Mix soups together and add enough broth to make it soupy.
Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Cover with soup and broth mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, drain and add salt.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and water.
Stir.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam, with 6 tortillas.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Add second layer of tortillas.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until the top is slightly brown.

title: drebby pie
directions: Place pecan chips and chocolate chips in bottom of uncooked pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and mix.
Pour over pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill. Garnish with whipped cream and fresh mint leaves, if desired. Makes 10 servings.

title: calico sauce
directions: Mix onion and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Melt the butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add the onion and green pepper and cook and stir until tender but not brown.
Add and stir in the flour. Gradually blend in the bouillon.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes until thickened.
Add and stir in remaining ingredients.
Good on cabbage, spinach and broccoli. Yield:
1 cup.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Press one package of rolls across bottom of pan.
Pinch together the separations.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread on the dough.
Unroll the 2nd package of crescent rolls and spread on top of creamed mixture.
Pinch together the separations.
Brush on egg white.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes (until crust is browned).

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together; stir in cornmeal.
Add milk, eggs and shortening.
Beat with rotary or electric beater for 1 minute or just until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, soda and water for 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir well.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved; let cool.
Add apples, celery and pecans.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pork fried rice or shrimp
directions: First, place your rice on to cook.
In a skillet, salt and pepper pork chops and fry until brown on each side.
Cut chops away from bone into small bite size pieces.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Then slowly cook bell pepper and onion until done.
Then add chops.
Let simmer until rice is done.
Mix rice and ingredients in saucepan all together in a big pan.
Serves about 4 people.

title: dried beef hors d'oeuvre
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 1-quart casserole 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Add boiling water, baking soda
to the dates or raisins.
Let this cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients thoroughly.
Combine this with the first mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans, filling 1/2 full.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and divide mixture in half.
Pat half of mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then remove from oven and spread with melted caramels that have been mixed with evaporated milk.
Then sprinkle on chocolate chips and nuts.
Top with other half of cake mixture and bake 18 minutes.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Stir all up at one time; let sit in refrigerator.
Add Cool Whip on top after congealed.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat together cheese, lemon juice and milk until smooth. Spread into graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling. Chill thoroughly.

title: roasted game hens with potato hash
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
To make hash, heat 1 tablespoon oil in a heavy skillet over high heat; add bell pepper, onion and celery.
Stirring often.
Cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon paprika, thyme, 2 tablespoons parsley, and salt and black pepper to taste.
Stir in potato.
Add broth; heat to boiling.
Lower heat to a simmer; partially cover pan.
Cook, turning occasionally, until potato is tender, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat, but keep warm till ready to serve.
Meanwhile, cut backbone from each hen with a knife or kitchen shears.

Rub hens all over with remaining 1 tablespoon oil; season with remaining 1 teaspoon paprika, and salt and black pepper, to taste. Heat an ovenproof skillet over high heat; brown hens, skin side up, 3 minutes.
Turn; brown 2 minutes more.
Transfer pan to oven; place another cast-iron pan or a brick wrapped with foil on top of hens.
Roast 12 minutes. Remove top pan or brick.
Turn birds skin side up; cook until firm, evenly brown, but still moist, about 7 minutes.
Mound hash on each of 2 plates; place a hen on each. Garnish with remaining 2 tablespoons parsley.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts about 30 minutes or until fork goes through easily.
Remove chicken from bone; cut in bite size pieces.
Spread on bottom of baking dish.
Mix soups and milk and pour on top of chicken.
Mix stuffing according to package, except for eggs and not as much water.
Sprinkle stuffing over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbling.

title: parmesan potato salad
directions: In a large serving dish, combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: chicken-bacon nuggets
directions: Remove skin and cut chicken in chunks.
In a medium bowl, mix chicken, marmalade, soy sauce, salt, ginger and garlic powder. Set aside.
Can let marinate overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix and chill the first 3 ingredients. Spread thin on large cookie sheet. Spread refried beans and then chunky salsa on top of this.
Add plenty of lettuce, tomato, cheese, olives and onion on top. Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 12.

title: deluxe carrot cake and cream cheese icing
directions: Generously oil and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients except for last four in a large bowl.
Pour into pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Test to check for doneness.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: bryan's bundles(individual serving whole meal in a bundle)
directions: Place each ground chuck patty on an 8 x 8-inch piece of aluminum foil.
Cover with potato, carrots and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Close foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Can be charcoal grilled for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add alternately milk and flour. Add vanilla.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Dribble coconut milk over layers.
Cover with whipped cream and fresh coconut.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk and sugar, then mix well. Combine flour, salt and baking powder, then add to wet ingredients and mix. Place 1 1/2-inches of oil in a frying pan and heat until hot (about 10 minutes). Using 1 cup of batter at a time, pour through funnel into the oil, making a crisscross pattern. When both sides are golden brown, put on a paper plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Recipe makes about 8 good-sized cakes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and set aside.
Cream shortening and add sugar, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Whip up oatmeal mixture and add to cream mixture.
Add dry ingredients. Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When done, spread with topping.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place artichokes (quartered) in bottom of 2-quart pretty baking dish. Add the layer of crabmeat (don't break lumps), then top with sauteed mushrooms. Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir 1 minute (do not brown), then add cream and whisk until slightly thickened. Add Worcestershire sauce, sherry, paprika, cayenne, pepper and salt. Cook until combined.
Pour sauce over mushrooms and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Best with buttered egg noodles or rice.

title: microwave artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes well.
Chop into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 8-inch square casserole.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes at 50% power.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 3 cups.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Mix until smooth and add to potatoes.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes. Stir frequently.
Serve.
Top with bacon crumbles.

title: margie's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture and blend.
Add the oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: new york style egg cream
directions: Place chocolate syrup into a 12 ounce glass.
Add milk, then seltzer.
Stir and drink.

title: italian beef
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add sliced beef.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve on French rolls with sweet or hot peppers.

title: beef-filled corn bread squares
directions: In skillet, cook the beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in catsup and salt.
Set aside.
In bowl prepare corn bread mix according to package directions (or prepare your own recipe).
Spread half of the batter in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon beef mixture over batter in pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Spread remaining batter over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until corn bread is done, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: burgers creole
directions: Shape meat into steaks.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: chicken in tomato tarragon cream
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
Heat butter in large saute pan until butter stops sputtering.
Place chicken pieces in the hot butter in the pan and cook until golden.
Brown second side, then add chopped shallots.
Continue cooking a minute or two, then add the wine.
Stir to dissolve browned particles in bottom of pan.
Add chopped tomatoes and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring for a few minutes, then add cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook over medium heat (stirring often) until thick.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Beat meringue and top pies.
Brown meringue in oven at 300° to 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season fryer with paprika.
Place all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan as listed with oleo in the middle and remaining ingredients scattered around oleo.
Place chicken on top of mixture and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef in skillet over medium heat; drain and set aside. Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth. Stir in beef, cheese, onion and pepper. Turn into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown
meat,
onions
and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 1 hour or longer if desired.
Serve with Mexican corn bread.

title: cajun shrimp casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter until vegetables are soft.
Add tomatoes and mushroom soup.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and shrimp.
Cook for 15 minutes more.
Add a little water if mixture is sticky.
Add rice and crab boil.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
